title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in Pyrex dish.
Slice onion over top of potatoes.
Spoon hamburger over onion and pour tomato soup evenly over mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together. Grease and flour square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients
and drop by tablespoon onto a well-greased griddle. Griddle about 3 minutes on each side or until brown.
Serve with applesauce.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Let raisins stand in hot water for 5 minutes; drain and pat dry.
Add raisins and applesauce to flour mixture.
Add salt, lemon juice and vanilla; mix.
Place dough in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool. These loaves freeze well.

title: mushroom and spinach soup
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms.
In medium saucepan, combine water, broth and carrot.
Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat and let simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms, spinach and tomato.
Cook covered on low heat an additional 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sherry and seasonings to desired taste.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Place each biscuit in a greased muffin cup, pressing to cover bottom and sides. Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples into buttered casserole, set aside. Mix together next four ingredients.
Stir in unbeaten egg. Mix well and sprinkle mixture over top of apples. Melt butter and dribble over top of apples.
Top all with a sprinkle of cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35-40 minutes longer.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Arrange apple slices in a greased baking dish.
In saucepan, mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, spices and water.
Place over low heat.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and lemon juice.
In separate bowl, mix remaining flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in remaining butter until consistency of cornmeal.
With a fork, stir in enough milk to make a soft dough.
Spoon onto apples, making 8 biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: tijuana omelet(j.r.'s special breakfast)
directions: Fry diced bacon and drain.
Beat eggs in bowl; add fried bacon, cheese, cream and jalapeno pepper and juice.
Return to frypan; stir and soft fry to your liking.
Serve with hot cakes. Serves 4.

title: punch
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade by directions on can.
Add Hawaiian punch and sugar.
Put ginger ale in just before getting ready to serve.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 gallons.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, baking soda and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add eggs and flour alternating.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: mama's cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread, add hot broth until juicy.
Saute celery and onions.
Add to corn bread, plus all other ingredients and spices.
Bake in 400° oven until juice cooks down.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare green pepper, celery and onion while macaroni cooks according to package directions; drain but do not rinse.
In small bowl combine mayonnaise, mustard, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper; slowly blend in milk; stir in butter and toss the dressing with the still warm macaroni.
Mix in vegetables; chill overnight.
Add scallions before serving.

title: butter pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Karo, brown sugar, melted margarine, salt and vanilla; blend well.
Arrange pecans on bottom of crust and pour filling over them.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Will set as it cools.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil, cool and cube potatoes.
Mix in all other ingredients and top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with stuffing
directions: Lay chicken breasts in single layer in a large baking dish. Put slice of cheese on each breast.
Mix soup and wine. Spread over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle stuffing over all. Drizzle butter on top. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, salt, milk, garlic salt, pepper, chili powder, onion, rice and meat.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place cheese on meat.
Spread remaining meat over cheese.
Make certain cheese is completely covered.
Spoon barbecue sauce over loaf.
Bake until meat is done, about 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 3/4 cup pineapple juice (drained from pineapple).
Add egg.
Beat until mixed.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes or until done; cool.
Pour remaining juice over cake.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add softened cream cheese.
Pour over cooled cake and spread evenly.
Sprinkle crushed pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread 9 ounces Cool Whip over pineapple and sprinkle coconut on top.
Chill well before serving.
Cake is better if frozen a day or so before eaten.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leftover makes good sandwiches.

title: italian-style meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, celery and onions.
Add beans; let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator, turning once or twice.

title: quick broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, just until thawed.
Place broccoli and sauce in blender and process until finely chopped.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk gradually and cook and stir until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and chicken bouillon. Add broccoli and simmer until heated through.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: granny smith apple dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Slice apples and enjoy with dip.

title: corn in the husk(microwave)
directions: Discard soiled outer portion of husks.
Soak corn in cold water 10 minutes; drain, but do not dry.
Arrange corn in spoke fashion on micro-proof plate.
Use Cook cycle and cook 11 to 12 minutes, re-arranging halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Peel and discard husks and silk.
Serve with butter, salt and pepper.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add Parmesan, salt, mustard, pepper, paprika and marjoram.
Stir until cheese melts.
Spoon sauce over broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Boil chicken for 1 1/2 hours.
Bone chicken and save broth. Mix ingredients. Add to chicken.
Use broth for desired thickness. Layer chips, cheese and mixture. Bake at 350° for
35 minutes.

title: cream of spinach soup(may be served hot or cold)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Transfer to a heavy saucepan.
Bring soup to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring frequently.
Ladle into bowls and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: fun pie
directions: Make ice cream pie.
It's easy.
Just press a quart of softened ice cream into a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.
Top it with your choice of ice cream sauce, nuts and pureed fruit and freeze.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream and chocolate.
It's delicious.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, simmer uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, heat through.
Serve over rice or poppy seed noodles.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: pilau de camarones (braised rice with shrimp and tomatoes)(dominican republic)
directions: Shell
the
shrimp.
Devein
them
by
making a shallow incision down
the backs with a small, sharp knife and lifting out the
black	or white intestinal vein with the point of the knife. Cut
the shrimp crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces and set them aside.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350°.
This will make about 12 very thin layers.
Use a couple of big serving spoons for each layer.
Put dried apples between each layer as you take them out.

title: wine punch
directions: Combine limeade, white wine and ginger ale in punch bowl. Serve with an ice ring and lime slices.

title: breakfast fajitas(good anytime!)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet; saute potato (may be previously baked or fried), onion, green pepper and mushrooms (if desired).
To the skillet, add beaten eggs and cheese.
Cover skillet to set eggs; cook over low heat until eggs are completely cooked.
Roll individual, warm tortilla shells with a slender slice of egg mixture, topped with salsa, cheese and any other additions you wish.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on top of double boiler until it thickens.
Store in refrigerator.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Boil
margarine,
sugar,
cocoa
and milk 2 minutes and remove from
stove.
Add	vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Beat thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: egg rolls
directions: Shred all vegetables.
Brown ground beef in pan; drain all grease.
Add vegetables to beef and cook for a few minutes. Vegetables should remain crisp.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch and salt.
Cook 3 minutes more.
Spread 1 tablespoon of filling in center of egg roll wrapper.
Fold 3 of the sides like a diaper. Moisten the edge of the fourth side with water; fold and seal edge.
Fry in oil until light brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix alternately the dry ingredients with mashed bananas. Raisins and coconut can be added.
Don't overmix.
Bake in 4 (5 x 3 x 2-inch) pans or 3 (2 x 4 x 8-inch) pans in 300° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: special k snack
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; pour over Special K and mix.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: meatballs for spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form into balls. Brown and add to sauce.

title: scotch tarts
directions: Blend butter, flour, egg, powder and sugar.
Carefully roll onto floured board.
Cut into squares and fill greased muffin tins.
Fill with pie filling.
Cut circle tops out of dough and place over filling.
Bake at 350° until golden, 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and top with cherry.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Then cut into round slices.
Mix together all the other ingredients for the marinade.
Do not cook this mixture.
Pour marinade over carrots and leave in the refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.
Then drain sauce and serve.
The marinade can be saved and re-used.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish. Cover with chopped onions. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the pork chops.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: oven-fried french fries
directions: Wet potato strips and coat with mixture of flour, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Melt the margarine in large cookie sheet. Place potatoes in margarine and bake about 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 more minutes.

title: homestyle pot roast
directions: You will need a large size (14 x 20-inch) oven bag.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off the bones.
Pick chicken off the bones.
Cook the spaghetti noodles; drain.
In large pan, mix spaghetti, chicken, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta.
Cook over low heat until cheese has melted.

title: creamy orange dessert
directions: Mix gelatin and water in 2 1/2 to 3-quart microwavable bowl. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows; microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
Add ice cream.
Stir with wire whisk until melted.
Stir in oranges; pour into 6 cup ring mold.
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
To unmold, dip in hot water 10 to 15 seconds.
Gently pull gelatin from edges with moist fingers.
Place moistened serving plate on top of mold.
Invert, holding mold and plate together.
Shake slightly to loosen.
Gently remove mold.

title: pudding chewy brownies
directions: Mix contents of pudding package with unsifted flour and baking powder.
Melt
oleo;
remove
from heat and add sugar. Beat
in eggs,
one
at a time.
Blend in vanilla and pudding mixture. Stir
in nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased 8-inch square
pan. Bake
at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut into bars.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Add a small amount of oil and mix well.
Add	small
amount of vinegar and mix well. Continue alternating oil and
vinegar.
Be	sure you start and finish with oil.
Use
an
electric mixer.	This can be stored without refrigeration.

title: baked three beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Cook onions in bacon drippings.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Crumble bacon and mix into beans.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine and put in 9-inch deep graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Mix all other ingredients well. Form into one large ball or two smaller balls. Roll cheese ball(s) in remaining pecans. Chill for 1 hour and serve with crackers.

title: island strawberry smoothie
directions: Place ingredients in blender in order listed. Blend for about 2 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Simmer broccoli, onion and margarine until broccoli is done. Add soup, cheese and rice and mix well. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground sirloin. Saute onion. Add salt, pepper and rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Freezes well. Reheats nicely in microwave.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool (large loaf pan).
Spread blueberry pie filling on cooled cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: marble fudge bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In 2-quart heavy saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
With wire whisk or spoon, beat in 2 cups sugar and 3 eggs until well blended.
With wooden spoon, stir in flour, salt, nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Spread evenly in pan.

title: dog biscuits your pets will love
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Roll in 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut into dog bone shapes, people shapes or just rectangles.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rye rounds
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Spread same on rye rounds. Sprinkle same with salad seasoning.
Place same under broiler and brown until light brown in color. Serve almost immediately. Be aware as it gets very, very hot, but is delicious.

title: salisbury steak(20 servings)
directions: Mix all real well.
Make into 4-ounce portions (shape into oblong football like shapes).
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes. Use regular brown gravy.
Add 1 (16-ounce) can of mushrooms per bag of gravy.
Top meat with gravy when serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop up artichoke hearts (in food processor, if available). Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie or quiche dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: zucchini with hominy
directions: In small amount of oil, saute zucchini, green onion and bell pepper.
Add jalapeno pepper with small amount of hominy liquid. Cook over low heat until zucchini is tender and flavors are blended (about 10 minutes).
Add salt if needed.
Turn off heat. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Let it melt, then serve.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Mix chile sauce and grape jelly together in pan.
Add mini sausages and simmer for at least 1/2 an hour.

title: double apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Add apples and raisins. Stir in apple juice, oil and eggs until moistened. Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pans. Serve warm.

title: anadama bread
directions: Combine water, salt, cornmeal and shortening.
Cook until thick; cool.
Combine and blend well the rest of the ingredients. Knead and let rise.
Punch down and form into 2 loaves.
Put in bread pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: grilled or oven stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; reserve caps.
Chop stems.
In medium saucepan, cook the chopped stems and onion in the 1 tablespoon butter just until tender.
Blend in flour, marjoram and pepper; add wine.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in ham and parsley.
Stuff mushroom caps with ham mixture.

title: breakfast sandwiches
directions: Spread butter on bread slices; place 4 slices, buttered side down, in a single layer in a greased shallow baking pan.
Top each bread slice with sausage and remaining bread slices, buttered side up.
Sprinkle with cheese and combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over sandwiches.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: stew for a crowd
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about 4 months.
Simmer slowly over medium heat.
Save trunk to store pieces in while cutting up.
Simmer about 3 weeks.
Add vegetables during last week.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 17-inch baking pan with crescent rolls, patting and stretching to fit.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: In food processor bowl, chop green onions; add spinach, mayonnaise and garlic salt.
Serve with Fritos.

title: pancit bijon
directions: Saute garlic in cooking oil; add onions, carrot and cabbage. Season with soy sauce and fry for 2 minutes.
Add broth and simmer; add kintsay.
When vegetables are cooked, mix in soaked and drained bijon and season with salt and m.s.g.
Garnish with chorizo and spring onions.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Slice and cook the carrots until tender; melt the butter and add ginger and maple syrup to the butter.
Simmer the carrots and the syrup mixture until glazed.
Stir frequently.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: First layer: Crush pretzels: mix with melted butter and sugar. Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan for 8 minutes at 400°; cool.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off grease.
In a crock-pot, melt cheese.
Add ground beef and tomatoes.
Stir well. Heat through.
Serve with chips.

title: beef burgundy stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour.
In Dutch oven, brown meat and garlic in hot shortening.
Add remaining ingredients, except vegetables.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender (about 30 to 40 minutes). Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: cabbage stuffed with ham and cheese
directions: Trim the loose outer leaves from a firm head cabbage.
Cut out enough from the stem end to make a deep well.
Prepare a filling by combining all ingredients.
Fill the center of the cabbage with this filling.
Cover it with a bowl and lid or wrap the cabbage in heavy foil and bake for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve it with Cheese Sauce (see recipe which follows).
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 15 minutes in 375° oven. Serve with crackers.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes. Prick with fork. Oil skins lightly. Bake at 400° for about 60 minutes or until done. Cut a slice from the top of each potato and scoop out the flesh. Whip or mash; add margarine, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Adjust milk until the potato mix is about like regular mashed potatoes. Then add the onions and cheese. Mix well.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions into large pot.
Add crushed garlic. Add chopped peppers (sliced jalapeno may be used).
Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Cook over low to medium heat until onions and peppers are done.
Juices will cook down.
Pour into jars and seal or put into jars and refrigerate.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Brown chicken lightly in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in deep Dutch oven; remove excess fat.
Add about 3 quarts of hot, salted water.
Simmer chicken until just tender.
Pour remaining bacon drippings into skillet; add flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown.
Add onion and garlic to roux (dark brown flour mixture for gravy); cook over low heat for about 5 minutes or until onion is wilted.
Add roux to chicken mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Cook for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Brown sausage lightly in skillet; drain.
Add shallots and parsley; stir into gumbo.
(Raw oysters and liquid from oysters may be added instead of sausage; cook long enough for oysters to get done.) Remove from heat.
Add file, stirring well.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls; spoon desired amount of rice into each bowl.
Yields 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add carrots, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry in skillet all ingredients except dough.
Let the dough rise.
Roll the bread dough into a large rectangle about the size of a cookie sheet.
Spread sausage mix and 1 pound of Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down on a greased cookie sheet.
Brush with oil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with chicken.
Cover with mushrooms and water chestnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs; blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Combine soups and pimientos; pour over the cheese slices.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, crumble bread crusts; toss with melted butter or oleo.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, place melted butter.
Add sugar, flour and milk; mix until dry ingredients are well moistened and smooth.
Add drained peaches and sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese flan
directions: Caramel: Put sugar in pan. Add water in center of sugar. Put on medium flame and leave until it turns into caramel. Immediately put caramel into baking pan/mold. Turn oven to 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put shortening, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over it to soften shortening.
Soak yeast in 1/2 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Add shortening mixture.
Add egg and stir in flour 1 cup at a time.
Refrigerate in a covered container overnight or several hours.
Remove from refrigerator about 2 hours before cooking.
Shape rolls and place in greased pan. Brush with melted butter.
Let rise.
Bake at 450° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken a la orange
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over or baste chicken often with mixture as chicken is baked on 325° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: giulio's spaghetti with sun-dried tomatoes and chicken
directions: Prepare and put aside in small dishes.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.
Take seeds out of plum tomatoes; cut into small pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Boil sun-dried tomatoes for 2 minutes; drain and chop them.
Place oil in saute pan.
When oil is hot, add chicken cubes and stir until cooked.
Add plum tomatoes, sun-dried tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Cook until all is done (about 1/2 hour).
Cook the spaghetti; drain and mix.
Add lots of grated cheese.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oats
and buttermilk.
Add rest of ingredients.
This is thick batter.
Serve with warm chunky applesauce.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While hot, punch holes in cake and pour condensed milk over it.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Beat until thick.
Add Cool Whip and coconut; spread over cake after it cools completely.
Sprinkle some coconut on top.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk and 1 teaspoon of salt and garlic salt in a large bowl; mix lightly until well blended.
Shape into 12 balls.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven; add onions and mushrooms; sprinkle with sugar.
Brown quickly; remove with slotted spoon to shallow pan.
Add meat balls to drippings in Dutch oven; brown.
Combine with vegetables.
Blend flour and remaining salt into drippings in pan. stir in beef broth until smooth, then wine and carrot.
Add bay leaf and vegetables and meat balls; cover, simmer 35 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add onion, and cook gently for 5 minutes. Blend in flour, stir in tomato sauce, add water, heat to boiling. Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: cheese dip
directions: Finely chop all peppers.
In a medium saucepan, stir together all ingredients with 1/2 of the peppers.
Heat thoroughly. Transfer to a serving bowl and sprinkle with remaining peppers. Serve with taco chips.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and beat until smooth.
Add next 8 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in parsley and pimento.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours until firm.
Shape into ball and cover with pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley, if desired.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 (12-inch) or 2 (9-inch) pizza pans with butter.
Prepare brownie mix as directed for fudgy brownies.
Stir in peanuts.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Place cabbage and green pepper in a large bowl.
Put remaining ingredients in blender and process until onion is well mixed.

title: pineapple, strawberry and cherry conserve
directions: Prepare berries and cherries; drain pineapple.
Slice orange very thin.
Combine fruits; weigh and add equal weight of sugar. Cook slowly until mixture thickens when a little is tested on a cold plate.
Pour into hot glasses and cover with paraffin.
This is delicious served with cream cheese and crackers.

title: savory rice
directions: Fry onion in butter.
Add mushrooms and heat gently.
Add soy sauce when hot and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box, then pour in bottom of a deep cake pan. Then pour pineapple over it.
Then fix your Jell-O as directed on box.
Then pour over the other mixture very slowly.
Put in refrigerator and let jell.

title: granny bea's candied peanuts
directions: Dissolve
sugar
in water in saucepan over medium heat. Add peanuts
and
continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook
until
peanuts are completely sugared (covered and
no
syrup
left).
Pour
and
spread over ungreased cookie sheet
and	bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally for even roasting.

title: english pea and corn salad
directions: May add watercress, nuts and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: iced green tomato pickles
directions: Soak for 24 hours 7 lbs. of sliced green tomatoes in 2 gallons of water in which 3 c. of lime have been dissolved. Drain and soak in fresh water for 4 hours, changing the water every hour. Drain, place in kettle 5 lbs. sugar, 3 pints of vinegar, and one tsp. each of cloves, ginger, allspice, celery seed, mace, and cinnamon. Bring this syrup to boiling, pour over the tomatoes, and let stand over night. In the morning boil for 1 hour and seal in glass jars. Green vegetable coloring may be used to make a clear green color.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread dough in a 16-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Set aside.
Slice strawberries.
Set aside.
Spread glaze over cookie top with 3/4 of strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip mixture.
Top with strawberries.
Serves 8.

title: christmas tree decorations
directions: Mix ingredients with 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Cook together over medium heat for 4 minutes, stirring all the time until it looks like wet mashed potatoes.
Cover with a cloth and let cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, egg, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Form balls and brown in skillet.
Slowly heat sauce with sugar and vinegar.
Place balls in sauce.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Saute all ingredients until cheese is melted and mixed well. Use on chips, eggs, etc.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: A great many husbands are entirely spoiled by mismanagement in cooking and so are not tender and good.
Some women keep them too constantly in hot water, others freeze them, others put them in a stew, others roast them, others keep them constantly in a pickle.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil on medium heat.
Add onions and cook until glazed, then add mushrooms.
Saut for about 5 minutes.
Add more olive oil if needed.
Add 8 oz. can tomato paste and water.
Add spices and mix.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt to taste.
Serve with pasta.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add salt, vanilla and eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and 3/4 cup buttermilk.
Add soda to remaining buttermilk and fold into mixture.
Bake in greased and wax paper-lined 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cut off heat for last 10 minutes. Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and finish cooling.

title: party scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients in larger roaster.
Bake at 250°
for 2 hours, stirring with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.
Be careful not to crush cereal. Pack in freezer bags and seal to store but do not freeze.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Allow cheese to get to room temperature.
Heat undiluted soup in pan over low heat 1 minute.
Add cream cheese to soup, stir to dissolve lumps.
Add gelatin to mixture; stir well.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and spoon into mold.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Add cheese soup and milk to onion.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until creamy.
Pour over macaroni and stir until mixed.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar and milk to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Add vanilla and peanut butter, then oats and cocoa.
Turn off heat and stir.
Drop in mounds on wax paper.
Refrigerate to harden faster.

title: chocolate-sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: grinder snacks
directions: Grind together raisins, figs and dates.
Add lemon juice to cracker crumbs.
Roll one rounded teaspoonful of fruit mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in cracker crumbs until coated.
Store in airtight container.
Yield 16.
Exchanges, 1 fruit.

title: bourbon marinade
directions: In a dish, combine all ingredients together.
Use the marinade for beef, chicken, shrimp or pork.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: judy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Soak chicken 4 hours overnight in sauce.
Drain chicken (but save the sauce).
Bake in a shallow pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Turn pieces over and baste with sauce often.
Ten minutes before turning off the heat, pour the rest of the soy sauce mixture on top.
Serve with chopped green onions and Chinese parsley.
Serves 10-12.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add milk. Cook until thick.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, add 3 tablespoons of sugar and beat.
Put on pie and brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Microwave cheeses and margarine on medium, stirring occasionally just until melted.
Combine milk and eggs.
Add gradually to the cheese mixture.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni and bake in a greased baking dish for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Combine sugar and water. Cook until it makes a long thread. Pour in thin stream over beaten egg whites; add vanilla. Beat until it starts to lose its gloss and is right consistency to spread. This frosting will remain soft.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir in chili powder and flour.
Add tomato sauce and 4 to 5 cans water.
Cook down on medium heat about 30 minutes.
Add beans.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Pack cabbage and salt in crock or jar.
Put cloth over and a plate and weight down (60° to 70° temperature).
Remove skum every other day for 10 to 12 days.
Fill jars and seal.
Water bath for 15 minutes after water comes to a boil.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Fry fresh garlic in oil.
Put tenders in egg and then flavored bread crumbs.
Fry and then put in Pyrex dish with lemon and tarragon vinegar.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes.

title: jello russian salad
directions: Put water in pan and bring to boil.
Add jello.
Mix in marshmallows and cream cheese; stir until melted.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes. Cook beef in fat. Add onion, chili powder and salt. Soften tortillas by dipping one at a time in hot Enchilada sauce. Spoon on filling. Roll, then arrange in shallow baking dish with seam side down. Pour on remaining sauce. Sprinkle with onion and cheese. Heat at 350° for 15-20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: chicken taco casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Boil fryer or chicken breasts.
Debone chicken and cut into chunks.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer floured tortillas, then chicken mixture and alternate mixture and cheese, then chicken mixture, onion and celery (chopped) and enough chicken broth to boil in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Add mushroom or chicken soup until done.
Layer all this and top with tortilla and cheese and pour chicken broth over this (bake until this bubbles).
Let cook at 325° until done.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs well.
Pour in the pie shells.
Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Put on top of butter mixture.
Spread pineapple tidbits over bananas.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Place cherries on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle chopped nuts and cherry halves on bottom of slightly greased 10-inch tube or spring-form pan.
Pour batter over.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool on rack.
Invert on serving plate.
Prick top of cake with toothpick.
Drizzle and brush glaze evenly over top and sides.

title: corn quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie crust for 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, heavy cream, salt, pepper, onion and corn; beat until well blended. stir in cheese.
Turn into partially baked shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes until custard mixture is almost set in center. Sprinkle with chopped chives, parsley or crumbled cooked bacon.

title: french chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate and water.
Stir and bring to a boil and cook until melted together.
Combine sugar and salt.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool, then add whipped cream, 1 tablespoon to a cup.
Pour into hot milk.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: whiskey wieners
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours or on top of stove for 2 hours.
The longer the better.

title: yankee doodle salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Cut beans into lengths to fill pint jars.
Pack beans into hot, scalded jars.
Add 1 chilli pepper, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed, 1/2 teaspoon dill seed and 1 clove of garlic to each jar.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush pie shell with egg white.
Prick well.
Chop bacon into 1-inch lengths.
Fry and drain well.
Scald milk to hasten cooking.
Cool slightly.
Beat together milk, eggs, spices and chives.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Pour custard mixture over bacon and cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cut shortening in until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Roll out to fit deep dish. Fill with fruit and sugar; dot with butter and strips of crust. Bake at 375° until crust is golden and filling is bubbly.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Mix liquid ingredients and pour over chicken in a baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: special k candy
directions: Spray a cake pan with Pam.
Place sugar and corn syrup in medium size saucepan and stir to combine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Special K cereal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares, eat and enjoy.

title: rice
directions: Combine rice, margarine and onion in skillet.
Brown, stirring constantly.
Pour into long baking dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over rice.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 20 minutes.
May need to add more water.

title: chicken tahitian
directions: Marinate chicken breasts overnight in mixture of orange juice, oil, ginger, curry powder, dry mustard and soy sauce in covered baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in marinade at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle almonds over chicken during last 10 minutes of cooking. Serve chicken on rice, garnished with pineapple chunks and avocado slices.

title: broccoli with cheese
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and mustard. Place broccoli in baking dish; spread the mayonnaise mixture over top.
Bake until sauce is melted and hot in 350° oven 15 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sauerkraut-peanut cake
directions: Mix
the
flour,
baking
powder,
soda, salt and cocoa together.
Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla,
water and kraut to creamed mixture.
Combine dry and liquid mixtures.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta shells.
Chop next 8 ingredients; mix with pasta.
Stir in dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: delicious vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: pleasure dip
directions: Cook meat and sausage together.
Add to cheese that has been melted in boiler.
Add diced Ro-Tel tomatoes and chili powder. Serve hot over chips and enjoy.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, Cool Whip and milk.
Pour over fresh sliced peaches that are arranged in a baked pie shell.

title: luscious apple rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Stir in 2 tablespoons margarine; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut 2/3 cup margarine into flour mixture with fork or pastry blender until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 4 to 5 times.

title: coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs. Beat well. Combine dry ingredients and buttermilk; mix well. Stir in walnuts, coconut and extract. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Pour hot syrup over hot cake. Keep in pan for 4 hours.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bars
directions: Heat
oven
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13
x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla. Beat
in
water
and egg.
Mix in flour, baking soda and
salt. Stir in peanuts and candies.
Spread dough in pan. Bake until light brown, 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Place margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan; melt margarine in oven.
Remove from heat.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
Shape each biscuit into a cinnamon twist by rolling it on a cutting board until it is long and pencil thin. Now tie each rope of dough into a knot.
Roll in the melted margarine in the baking pan.
Roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix and serve on slaw when ready to serve.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Combine margarine, water and cocoa in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil stirring occasionally.
Combine sugar and baking soda in a bowl, add chocolate mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed till thoroughly combined.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and beat for one minute.
Batter will be thin. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: buttermilk pie(rich and delicious!)
directions: Beat eggs; combine sugar and flour.
Stir into eggs.
Add melted margarine and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
After 25 to 30 minutes baking time, insert knife in center of filling.
If it comes out clean, it's done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add corn bread mix last. Bake at 350° to 375°. Makes 11 x 13-inch pan or 12 muffins.

title: 6-layer candy
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 15-inch pan. Spread each layer over last one, beginning with crumbs. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 2 hours and cut into bars.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spoon dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven about 10 minutes.

title: crisp barbecue chicken
directions: Season flour with salt and black pepper.
Remove yellow fat from chicken parts as well as possible (leave skin on).
Wash chicken and drain.
Roll well in batter.
Fry until golden brown and crisp.
Drain oil from chicken and place in baking dish which has been buttered.
Pour liberal amount of barbecue sauce over chicken until thoroughly coated.
Bake in 325° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in pan.
Bring to a boil and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme and chopped nuts.
Stir well until mixed.
Pour into well buttered large pan until cool enough to cut into pieces.

title: black cherry jello
directions: Add hot water to jello. Place bowl in sink of cold water until cool.
Then add firm bananas, 1 can of cherries with juice and other ingredients.
Do not substitute!
This is wonderful.

title: super bubble solution
directions: Mix a solution of one part glycerine and two parts water. (Most small projects will require 8 ounces of glycerine.) Loosely layer individual leaves into a glass or plastic container.
Pour glycerine solution over the leaves, making sure all surfaces are covered.
Secure container with a lid or plastic wrap.
Store containers of leaves out of direct sunlight.
Every few days tilt container to gently mix solution and assure all leaves are covered.

title: mock sausage patties
directions: Mix together beef, lemon juice and rind, bread crumbs, sage, ginger and broth.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Form into 8 patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Brush a heavy skillet with vegetable oil and set over heat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Put in the sausage patties and cook 7 or 8 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.
Yield:
8 patties.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine jello with hot water and add pineapple.
Set in refrigerator to partially congeal.
When slightly congealed, mix with Cool Whip, sour cream and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Pour into mold and let congeal.
This will keep several days under refrigeration.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes; arrange in glass casserole. Sprinkle on flour, salt and chopped onion.
Pour milk over all. Dot with butter.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Re-cover and continue cooking on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Let stand.

title: slender french fries(low-fat and heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 425°.
Baking Time: 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add to shortening mixture. Blend in oats. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake in moderate oven at 350°F for 12 to
15 minutes.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk (not evaporated) evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stir constantly until sauce is thick and clear.
Makes 2 cups.
Can be used to cook chicken, pork, beef, duck or with wontons.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Combine
sugar,
butter,
flour
and
milk in saucepan. Bring to	a
full
boil and boil hard for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove
from
heat and add remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Drop by teaspoons on foil or greased cookie sheet or for bars, put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole for buffet
directions: Precook chicken breasts.
Remove in good size pieces from bones.
Grease a casserole.
Put chicken in bottom.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Mix soup and sour cream with onion and mushrooms.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This can be put together the day before and baked when needed.
It also freezes well.

title: caramel cheerios bars
directions: Melt caramels, marshmallows and butter in pan on medium heat; stirring often.

title: broccoli-nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water. Drain.
Mix with next 5 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Mix bread crumbs with margarine and spread over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter and pour in bottom of pan. Beat remaining ingredients 20 minutes; pour over graham crackers.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut steak into thin slices while partially frozen.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate beef overnight.
Drain and dehydrate jerky on racks in food dehydrator or oven (200°) for 8 to 12 hours.
When done, seal tightly.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine. Mix with flour and nuts. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and lemon flavoring. Fold in Cool Whip. Leave enough to spread on top. Spread on crust. Mix pudding and milk. Stir until thick. Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: candied yams
directions: Drain potatoes, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Place potatoes in baking dish.
Mix together all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are soft.

title: lamb couscous
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. of the oil in a large saucepan and fry the onion for 4-5 minutes until softened.
Add the meat and fry over moderate heat until evenly browned.

title: rainbow rocky road drops
directions: Can add coconut or other flavored chips to dry mixture in place of listed ingredients.

title: cranberry orange scones
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray with cooking spray the sides and bottom of deep round cooking dish like a pie dish.
Place beef mixture in dish and shape in circle so does not touch sides.
Cover with wax paper or lay Ziploc bag on top and place in microwave. Cook at Medium for 20 to 24 minutes.
Drain liquid and spread more barbecue sauce on top.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins, in ungreased 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan; mix well.
Cook in microwave oven at High for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light golden brown, stirring every 2 minutes of cooking.
Stir in raisins and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, and salt; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook until soft ball is formed when dropped into water. Add vanilla, peanut butter, and margarine. Beat until it loses some of its gloss. Quickly spread in a lightly buttered 8 or 9 inch pan.

title: hot and spicy chicken
directions: Clean chicken and put in bowl.
Pour in 2 cups of cider vinegar.
Pour in 2 cups of hot sauce.
Put in refrigerator and marinate for 2 to 3 hours.
Add seasons.
Preheat cooking oil in fryer (or deep pot).
Dip chicken in flour and then into hot cooking oil.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and crushed crackers.
Put in 9-inch buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Beat 1 package Dream Whip. Cover pie with Dream Whip and sprinkle with frozen coconut.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in plastic container with tight lid.
Use 1/3 cup for each cup boiling water.

title: perky punch
directions: Place liquid ingredients into an electric percolator.
Place the spices in the basket.
Complete the percolator cycle.
Serve hot.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in foil-lined pan.
Prepare brown gravy according to instructions on envelope.
Pour gravy over meat and vegetables.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: russian salad
directions: Cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix with pineapple and mayonnaise.
Add carrots and nuts.
Mix Jell-O in boiling water. Add cheese mixture and blend.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: buckeye bars
directions: In a microwave, soften peanut butter and butter; then mix together.
Add graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Mix well and press into the bottom of a 9x13-inch pan.

title: banana boats
directions: Cut V-shaped wedge lengthwise in each banana.
Fill groove with miniature marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Wrap each banana in foil.
Bake until warm, about 10 minutes, at 450°.
Use as many bananas as you need servings.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground meat and onion.
Pour in all the remaining ingredients and stir.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve hot with Fritos and cheese or tortilla chips.

title: nut fudge(unscrambled)
directions: In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat, stir together the sugar, cream, chocolate and syrup until sugar and chocolate are melted.
Continue cooking very slowly, stirring often until mixture reaches 238° on a candy thermometer, a half teaspoon dropped into cold water will form a soft ball that flattens on removal from water.
May take an hour.
Take off heat; add butter, but do not stir.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beat with a wooden spoon until it has lost almost all its gloss.
Takes considerable beating.
Stir in nuts; turn into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and remove with a small metal spatula.
Arrange on plate.
Cover with cake dome or bowl. Leave at room temperature and the outside of fudge will dry a bit, but the inside will stay creamy for several days.

title: golden nectar punch
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed on cans.
Add pineapple juice, apricot nectar and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until chilled. Then just before serving, stir in ginger ale.

title: goof proof fudge(microwave)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into microwave.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir and pour in a buttered dish.

title: pepper jelly
directions: *Remove seeds from both peppers; cut into large pieces.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage as if for cole slaw.
(Do this the night before you plan to eat the salad.)
In a large bowl, put 1/5 cabbage layered with 1 tablespoon salt.
Continue to layer cabbage and salt 5 times until all cabbage is gone.
Cover with a clean dish towel; leave on counter overnight.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over whole bran cereal.
Mix well.
Cool. Stir in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir cooled bran mixture into creamed mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients just to barely moisten (batter will not be smooth); don't overmix. Refrigerate overnight.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Makes 3 dozen.
Store batter in tightly covered container in refrigerator; can be stored up to 3 days.

title: dilly beans
directions: Snap off stem ends of beans.
Pack into 4 sterilized pint jars to which you have added 1 large dill head and a sliced medium garlic clove.
Bring vinegar, water, salt and cayenne pepper to a boil.
Pour over beans.
Seal; process 10 minutes in hot water bath.
Do not use quart jars.

title: cherry yogurt smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients. Cover and process until blended well. Pour into chilled glasses. Serve immediately. Yield: 3 servings.

title: tuna noodle
directions: Put sauce mix, tomatoes, water and salt in pan.
Blend, boil, reduce heat and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to pkg. and combine noodles, sauce, tuna (or beef) and 1 cup of the cheese.
Toss lightly to blend.
Put in 2-1/2 qt. casserole, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 min.
Remove cover and bake 10 min. more.
(If you use hamburger - brown beef in skillet and crumble meat good; when done, drain.)

title: turkey-apple salad
directions: In medium bowl, gently stir together Swanson premium chunk turkey, apple, celery and raisins.
In cup, stir together dressing and brown sugar; pour over turkey mixture.
Toss gently to coat. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: 10 o'clock rolls
directions: Cool milk to lukewarm.
Add salt, sugar, oil, yeast and flour. Mix well.
Turn out in greased bowl and cover with wax paper. Let rise 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board and cut into rolls. Put in greased pan and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: brownie nugget cookies
directions: Place cocoa in a saucepan and gradually add milk, stirring well.
Stir in the sugar and oleo; bring the mixture to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats and peanut butter. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into battered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish or pan.
Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over low heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in olive oil.
Add meat and cook over medium heat until done.
Spoon off fat and discard.
Add can of soup and chili powder; simmer on low for 5 to 7 minutes.
Spoon onto buns and serve with corn and potato chips or potato salad.
Easy 1 pan meal.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Place green beans in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in other ingredients except onion rings.
Cover.
Microwave on 100% power for 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after half the cooking time.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat and put with rest of ingredients in crock-pot.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 275°.

title: peach cheese tarts
directions: Whip cheese and condensed milk.
Whip again.
Stir in lemon juice and continue beating until thickened.
Pour into tart shells and chill.
Place sliced peaches in shells.
Melt preserves with sugar.
When sugar is dissolved, pour glaze over peaches.
Top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo for 3 minutes.
Add water, cubes, broccoli and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.
Add milk and cheese; cook until cheese melts.

title: jello-pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: lana's chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch strips.
Combine salt and cayenne pepper.
Sprinkle on chicken.
Place flour in plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces one at a time.
Shake to coat lightly.
Heat Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Cook and stir chicken until no longer pink.
Remove to side dish with slotted spoon.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper to skillet.
Cook and stir on medium-high heat 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, ketchup, thyme, bay leaf and chicken broth.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add chicken and parsley.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes longer. Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings. Contains 460 calories, fat 12 g (108 cal or 23% of total calories), sat fat 1 g (<5% of total calories), carb 54 g, protein, 33 g, chol 65 mg and sodium 540 mg.

title: stuffed mushrooms parmesan
directions: Clean mushrooms. Reserve stems. Chop and reserve. Melt butter. Add onion, green pepper, garlic, pepperoni and chopped mushroom stems. Cook until tender, but not brown. Add crackers, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper. Mix well. Stir in chicken broth. Spoon stuffing into mushroom caps. Place in a shallow pan with 1/4-inch water. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In saucepan combine sugar, shortening and molasses.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and decorate as desired.

title: nacho's
directions: Brown ground beef until done.
Pour in pinto beans.
Pour taco chips in large bowl.
Pour beef mixture over the chips.
Put the nacho cheese over this and melt.
Add sour cream.

title: savory beef and vegetable stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge beef.
Cook bacon in Dutch oven until crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper and reserve. Brown sliced onion in drippings, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon to small bowl and reserve.

title: creamy swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper and brown lightly in skillet. Add onions, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Pour over steak (soup may need to be thinned with water to form a thick gravy).
Simmer until steak is tender.

title: crab bake
directions: Crush the potato chips and finely chop the pimiento.
In a large saucepan, warm the 2 soups to blend well.
Add the seasoned salt.
Remove the tough tendons from the crabmeat and flake.
Add the crab, chopped hard-cooked eggs, pimiento, crushed potato chips and almonds to soups.
Mix well.
Transfer to a buttered baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: linda's cherry salad
directions: Mix drained fruit, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice. Stir in cherry pie filling.
Fold into Cool Whip.

title: rice pudding(6 servings)
directions: Mix slightly the beaten egg yolk, 3 tablespoons sugar, tapioca and salt in saucepan.
Add milk and cook, stirring frequently, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Beat egg white until stiff. Beat remaining sugar in gradually.
Add to hot mixture with raisins, rice and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Cool.

title: creamwiches
directions: Toast waffles; cool.
In a small bowl mix marmalade with nuts. Spread over one side of waffles.
Cut ice cream into 4 slices; sandwich one slice between two waffles, with marmalade towards inside.
Top with additional marmalade and pecans, if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder, sugar, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Then add corn oil, eggs, water and canned pumpkin.
Mix well.
Then blend in dates and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dissolve sugar over medium heat. Add pecan halves and continue to cook stirring frequently.
Cook until pecans are completely sugared with no syrup left in pot. Spread on wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Debone chicken.
Reserve broth.
Combine soups, chilies, spices, Tabasco and broth; blend well.
Cover bottom of 3-quart dish with 2 cups of chips.
Put 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of sauce, then cheese.
Repeat.
If dry, add more broth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper, egg and minced onions together.
Roll into small balls about the size of a walnut or smaller; brown thoroughly.
While you are browning the meatballs, place the grape jelly and chili sauce in a fairly large cooker and heat until bubbling.
When meatballs are browned, place in cooker with chili sauce and jelly and simmer for several hours (the longer the better).

title: fall punch
directions: Refrigerate 1/2 of the cider.
Put the other 1/2 of cider in saucepan on low heat for 15 minutes with spices.
Strain spices.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Microwave Dish: Put oil in 2 or 3-quart casserole or baking dish. Add beef and toss so that meat is cooked with oil. Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring twice (cook power 7). Add tomatoes; cook, covered, 5 minutes, stirring once. Add green peppers; cook, covered, 6 minutes stirring once. Serve with rice or chow mein noodles. Yields 4 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter with garlic salt.
Add flour; mix well.
Do not burn.
Add milk; boil all until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Prepare lemonade as directed on cans.
Pour into punch bowl. Add and mix thawed strawberries.
(If fresh berries are used, crush 1 1/2 cups and add 1/2 cup of sugar; let stand 1/2 hour.) Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.
Yields 32 servings, 1 1/2 gallons.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine yeast and water.
Let stand about 5 minutes; then stir until yeast dissolves.
Add milk, egg, margarine, sugar and salt to yeast mixture; beat well with a spoon.
Mix in all-purpose flour and whole wheat flour.
Scrape the dough down from sides of the bowl to form a ball.
Cover with a clean dish towel and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Gradually add milk, sugar, salt, pepper and corn.
Cook thoroughly.
Take off heat and add egg, stirring constantly.
Put in a greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer sauerkraut, tomatoes, Thousand Island dressing, Polska kielbasa, Swiss cheese and rye crackers. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish (will take a large one or two small casserole dishes).
Bake for 2 hours in 325° oven.

title: patsy's dressingbetter than leo and willie's!  remember?
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Refill mayonnaise jars with dressing and chill.
Improves with age.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix well, in heavy saucepan, pudding, sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook and stir to an all-over boil.
Lower heat.
Stir and boil slowly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix water with jello; pour milk into cottage cheese and whip. Add mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour into oblong dish and refrigerate.

title: church filling(for 100 to 125 people)
directions: Cut bread up into 1/2 cubes.
It is good to do this a day ahead so they can dry out.
Saute onions and celery in the butter. Cook potatoes.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk, eggs, bread and other ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in hot water until you can stick a knife through them.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out potato.
Add all other ingredients to potatoes; mix well.
Put mixture back into potato shell.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in warm oven or microwave until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: beef jerky
directions: Season meat with pepper and salt.
Soak meat for 24 hours in mixture above.
Dry.
Works well for deer and elk.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: oriental salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine all the oil, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Set aside to serve with the salad.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt into a mixing bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into flour until a cornmeal type mixture is present.
(Use pastry cutter for best results.) Pour milk into mixture and mix with fork until all flour is moistened. (Sometimes more milk may be required if flour amount is too stiff.)
Pour dough onto floured surface and roll out to 1/2-inch thick or personal preference.
Place in baking sheet and bake at 425° until golden brown on top.

title: orange ricotta cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, combine cheese, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, 2 tablespoons liqueur, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Heat remaining 1 teaspoon liqueur with marmalade.
Spread about 3/4 on top of cheesecake.
Top with orange slices, then remaining marmalade mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix this mixture with a fork; drop onto cookie sheet with spoon.
Space apart. Grease pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle powdered jello over cottage cheese. Drain oranges and pineapple; add to cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut orange slices and dates into small pieces. Roll in 1/2 cup flour to coat. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Mix well. Add baking soda to buttermilk, then add flour and buttermilk to mixture. Add nuts, candy pieces and dates. Stir in coconut. Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Add cake mixture. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, dry Jell-O and mayonnaise. Pour boiling water into mixture and stir until dissolved.
Chill.

title: burger stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions, cook in boiling salted water 30 minutes or until tender yet firm.
Drain and cool.
Slice off top third of each onion.
Cut out centers to make cups.
Chop 1/2 cup of the centers and saute in Wesson oil with beef and green peppers for 5 minutes. (Save remaining onions for use in other dishes.)

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine chicken broth, chicken, 1 cup milk, carrots, onion, garlic, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Over medium heat, cook until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add peas last. Add noodles to chicken and vegetable mixture. Cook 30 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: roasted garlic and warm goat cheese appetizer
directions: Cut off the top third of the pointed end of the garlic.
Use a paring knife to cut any side cloves that are not exposed.
Put heads of garlic, clove sides up, in a baking dish.
Top with herbs, butter and oil.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(They can be made anytime and reheated.)

title: ground pork and shrimp stir-fry
directions: Cook
spaghetti
according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Combine soy sauce, cornstarch and 1 cup water; set aside. Heat
cooking
oil
in
wok or electric skillet on medium
high heat.
Thoroughly
cook pork with ginger, garlic and red
pepper. Add
green onion and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce mixture; cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Pour over noodles.
Toss to combine.

title: drop-in company's meal
directions: Either on stovetop or in crock-pot, combine first 7 ingredients.
Let simmer until cheese is melted and ingredients stirred. Allow guests to dip this mixture over their plate of taco chips.
May also be garnished with shredded lettuce (optional).

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, add pecans last.
Pour into pie shell and bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.

title: hungarian potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on and hard-boil 6 eggs.
Peel potatoes and slice into a casserole in layers with the eggs.
Put 1/2 the potatoes on the bottom layer, then 1/2 the eggs, next the last half of the potatoes and top with the last 1/2 eggs.
Mix sour cream, melted butter and Accent.
Pour this over top of potatoes and eggs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: partridge with garlic
directions: *Remove garlic skins by dropping cloves into boiling water for a minute, then peeling.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Blend the cake mix, apricot nectar, oil, sugar and eggs on low speed for approximately 1 minute.
Then mix on high speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bob evans salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar; mix by hand.
Add onion and blend by hand.
Add celery seed and corn syrup.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy skillet eggplant
directions: Place all ingredients except cherry tomatoes in skillet. Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 3-5 minutes. Serve hot or cold. Serves four.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cover bottom of crust with meat and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serve hot as main luncheon dish with a salad.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Start with four drops of mint flavoring.
Add flavoring and color carefully, as desired. Knead until pie dough consistency.
Add sugar to make softer, or decrease sugar for firmer consistency.
Take small pinch and roll into ball; roll in sugar.
Press into mold.
Remove excess and unmold at once onto waxed paper.

title: all-around good dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good served with crackers, vegetables, fruits and almost anything.

title: breakfast casserole(low cholesterol, low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey with Italian seasoning, garlic and onions.
Cut bread into cubes.
Place cubed bread in 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle turkey over bread.
Then sprinkle cheese over the bread and turkey.

title: banana split cake(seven layers)
directions: Mix margarine,
eggs,
confectioners
sugar and vanilla and beat 20 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Then layer in order: pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: incredible nut mix
directions: Mix all together.
This
recipe
makes	a lot.	Give as gifts packed in pretty tins.
A great hostess gift!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes or put in crock-pot on low.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken; mix rest of ingredients well and pour over chicken and rice.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours; remove cover for 20 minutes.
Bake until brown and tender.
Test for doneness; may take less time.

title: exceptionally good chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Dilute soup with 1/4 can of water and pour over chicken. Cover evenly with dry dressing/stuffing mix and dab with margarine.
Bake, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake a few more minutes.

title: shortbread drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg yolk, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix in raisins.
Drop by small teaspoons onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil, covered, for 20 minutes. Cool to room temperature.
Add 1 qt. vodka and 1 ounce almond flavoring.
Mix well.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Remove the stems from the poke sallet.
Place in a large pan and parboil the greens, letting the greens cook down.
Add a little soda to make the greens cook better.
Boil until the greens go down and the water looks green, about 3 minutes or longer. Drain off the water.
Place the poke in a large pot and add just enough water to keep the poke from sticking.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: bohemian stuffed roast pork
directions: Score the surface of the loin with a knife.
Mix the salt, pepper, sage and garlic; rub the surface with the spice mixture. Stand the loin on end.
Using a large 10-inch knife, skewer the roast lengthwise.
Remove the knife and begin stuffing prunes into the slot.
Pack the prunes in as tightly as possible.
When you can't stuff any more into the roast, secure both ends of the opening with toothpicks.
Place the pork in a pan, add about 1/2 cup water and cover with foil.
Put in a 375° oven and roast for about 1 hour and 45 minutes or until the internal temperature is over 180°.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes before carving.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic cloves over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain grease. Place mixture in 5 qt. slow cooker. Stir in beans and remaining ingredients. Cook on high 3 to 4 hours or on low 5 to 6 hours. If cooking on top of stove, simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate-tipped long cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add brandy, vanilla and salt, mixing well.
Add flour, stirring until blended.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Put in the pie crust. Freeze overnight.
Place washed strawberries on top before serving.

title: mom's (ruth davis) fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples with sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with apples and sugar.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Top with Caramel Icing.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Serve with celery, carrot sticks, cauliflower, broccoli flowerets, squash and cucumber slices.
Use any other fresh vegetables that may be in season.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Place the potatoes on a baking sheet in a 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes. Cool to room temperature.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, water, eggs, peanut butter and 1/2 of package of cake mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining cake mix and stir until well mixed. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 3-inches apart.
Press with granulated sugar and fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Put chicken broth and soup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken cubes.
In another bowl, mix margarine, flour and milk to form batter.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mushroom-wine sauce
directions: Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Cook mushrooms, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper in margarine about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in wine.
Cook over medium-high heat about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced by half.
Stir in whipping cream and heat to boiling.
About 1 cup sauce; 55 calories per tablespoon.

title: sherry-mushroom chicken
directions: Mix mushroom soup and sherry wine and pour over chicken in a baking pan.
Add sauteed mushrooms on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Good over noodles.

title: cherry rhubarb jelly
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar and let set overnight or until sugar turns to liquid.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Dice up fruit pie filling and add to rhubarb.
Simmer well and add 2 packages of jello.
Stir well until all is dissolved.
Put in containers and freeze.
Makes 10 1/2 cups of jam.

title: heavenly casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in small amount of oil.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in lightly sprayed 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and sliced almonds.
