Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken-vegetable patties
directions: Grate celery and onion.
In bowl, mix grated vegetables with rest of ingredients.
Shape mixture into four 3/4 inch thick patties.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in 2 tablespoon salad oil, or spray with cooking spray, cook patties about 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked throughout, turning once.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased cake tin.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
Into one pour cooking oil, in another vanilla and in the third one put vinegar.
Over all pour water.
Beat with a fork until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice or serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: candy pecans
directions: Mix water, sugar and Karo.
Cook to 240°.
Cut fire off and add vanilla, marshmallows and pecans.
Stir until mixture begins to sugar.
Pour out into greased pan and separate with fork.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: In a pan, mix the juice from pineapple, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling and pour over jello in bowl and stir well.
Break up cranberry with a fork and stir into jello. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in celery and pineapple.
Nuts optional.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large saucepan bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in noodles and butter sauce.
Boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally (4 minutes).
Stir in vegetables and tuna.
Continue to boil over medium heat 4 minutes, or until vegetables and noodles are tender.
Put into serving dish and top with cheese.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice peeled potatoes very thin.
Melt butter or margarine in electric frypan.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Layer in the potatoes. Sprinkle with the other cup sugar and 1/2 cup liquid.
Simmer, covered, until the potatoes are done and syrup turns slightly thick.
Do not stir but shake pan often.
Watch for scorching. Add more liquid if necessary.
Pour into greased casserole and serve or store covered to warm later.

title: file gumbo(servings:  6)
directions: Roux:
Put 3 tablespoons of olive oil in cast-iron skillet over high heat until start to smoke.
Sprinkle in hot oil, while whisking 3 tablespoons of flour.
Continue to whisk or roux will burn.
Cook until desired darkness of flour.
I like a dark roux. Remove from heat and add green onion and salt, pepper and cayenne. Continue to mix.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in casserole dish, which has been sprayed with non-stick spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together until sugar is melted. Add peanut butter; mix well. Add Rice Krispies. Press into buttered 9 x 13 pan.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes until small. Squeeze all juice out of spinach. Mix all ingredients and heat until warm.

title: grandma martha's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in 1 whole egg and 2 egg yolks.
Sift together and add salt, baking powder, flour and vanilla.
Roll out dough.
Cut out with a cookie cutter.
Sprinkle top with white sugar and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked pears
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, pare, halve and core firm pears. Arrange pears, hollow side up, in a shallow dish.
Combine 1/2 cup boiling water, 1/4 cup brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over pears and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, until tender, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese mold
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased 4 cup ring mold.
Chill overnight.
Just before serving, unmold and fill ring with 1 cup strawberry preserves.
Surround with Ritz crackers.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine the margarine, water and chocolate squares in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.

title: cindy's summer delight dessert
directions: Mix all together except marshmallows.
After everything is well mixed, put in refrigerator to cool.
Before serving, add the marshmallows and mix again.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Shape mixture in a loaf baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover top with tomato sauce before meat is done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat eggs until fluffy and add. Sift all dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add milk, bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in two greased, floured pans about 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together for 20 minutes (no less) the powdered sugar, eggs, 2 sticks butter and vanilla.
Spread this on crust.
Slice bananas lengthwise; lay on top of this. Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas, then add cherries and nuts. Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: tossed salad
directions: Clean vegetables and cut up.
Use very large bowls.
Mix in huge bowl by hand, cut to bite size tomatoes, cucumbers and lettuce.
Store in gallon Ziploc bags to keep leftover.
Use twice a day one bowl.
Can dilute evenly oil and vinegar for dressing, use none or favorite kind.

title: paprika ham(great for leftover ham)
directions: Mix tomato sauce with mustard, paprika and onion.
Add ham; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat slightly. Serve on noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Toss ingredients together. Chill. Serve in lettuce-lined salad bowl. Garnish with pimento strips. Serve with French dressing.

title: taco snack
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Mix together.
Spoon out into baking dish.
Pour salsa over first layer.
Add shredded lettuce.
Next, sprinkle taco cheese over lettuce.
Finally, add diced tomatoes. Refrigerate.

title: prune cake and sauce
directions: Combine sugar, oil, and eggs in mixing bowl; beat on medium speed with electric mixer 1 minute.
Dissolve soda and buttermilk; set aside.	Combine flour and spices; add to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, prunes, and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean; cool.

title: special seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Spread with frosting.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; serve on a bed of salad greens.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.
Goes great with chips, pretzels or raw vegetables.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon; add nuts.
Add pineapple after draining juice.
Cut up oranges in small bits.
Mix all ingredients with the Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shells.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: green sauce for burritos, enchiladas
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add bouillon cube (crushed), milk, 1 tablespoon of onion flakes, garlic salt and cumin.
Simmer to thicken sauce, stirring often.
Add grated cheese and stir to melt.
Stir in green chilies and heat until hot throughout.
Pour over enchiladas, burritos or whatever you like.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add apples.
Mix well; pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and shortening, then eggs.
Flour nuts in flour; add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add grated apple.
Pour into greased loaf pan.

title: pignolia cookies
directions: What I do is open a large, brown paper bag and sprinkle all the nuts on it.
Then drop by small spoonfuls of dough on nuts and roll.

title: brownie muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Fill greased or paper baking cup-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Bring the chicken broth to a boil.
Add potatoes, onion and leek.
Reduce the heat and simmer, covered, until the vegetables are tender.
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Stir in the flour and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Heat the milk and add it to the butter and flour mixture, whisking until the mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.
Add the stock and vegetables.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.

title: pineapple chiffon salad
directions: In small saucepan, bring pineapple with juice to boil.
Add powdered jello and stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk slowly. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch pan and chill until set.

title: john ben getty
directions: Brown meat and onions until done (can add pepper).
Add soups and corn or peas.
Mix well.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and blanch; add to meat mixture.
Grease large baking dish (12 x 18-inch).
Pour in mixture.
Cover with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, peanut butter and sugars until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until smooth. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; stir until soft dough forms. Stir in chocolate chips. Divide dough into thirds. Shape each into a 7-inch roll. Wrap in plastic wrap. Store in freezer. Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices. Bake in 375° oven on an ungreased baking sheet 7 to 9 minutes, until brown.

title: holiday tea
directions: Steep tea bags with water.
Add 1 cup sugar, orange juice and lemon juice and stir.
Add spice and candy.
Simmer until candies have melted.
Strain tea through a fine cloth.
This keeps refrigerated well.

title: italiano chicken and potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of roaster.
Place potatoes in bottom of roaster.
Sprinkle each piece of chicken on both sides with paprika, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place chicken on top of the potatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: italian sesame seed cookies
directions: Grease pan.
Mix dry ingredients; cut in margarine until real fine.
Add eggs (hold back 1 egg white).
Add almond flavoring. Knead until dough is all mixed and firm.
It should not be sticky.

title: chocolate almond pie(for diabetics)
directions: In a food processor, combine wafers, sweetener and butter. Pulse until blended.
Add egg white; pulse until moistened.
Press onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 370° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: easy baked turkey
directions: Season inside and outside of turkey with salt and pepper. Dissolve paprika in hot water.
Blend in peanut oil.
Baste turkey generously with oil mixture, greasing well.
Place turkey in bag, breast side up.
Tie ends of bag.
Place bag in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes per pound.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat instant pudding and 1 cup of fruit juice until thick and clear.
Add fruit and refrigerate.
(Bananas will not darken if made in advance.)

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain and flake salmon and crush bones.
Mix all ingredients well (except crumbs).
Divide into desired number of patties (I usually do 7 or 8) and shape carefully.
Roll in crumbs and let set a bit.

title: easy hobo stew
directions: Simmer for about one hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baked shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then bake 35 minutes at 300°.

title: tarragon sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat; add cornstarch, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in half and half until smooth.
Return to heat; stir constantly and bring to a boil.
Cook one minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve sauce over pork chops.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients to make batter.
Pour into baking pan.
Do not stir. Add fruit; do not stir.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Batter will cook up over fruit.
Makes 9 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Put salt on cabbage, onion and pepper. Let stand 30 minutes and drain off water. Mash with hands. Add sugar. Cover and put in fridge.

title: ham strata
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Line a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with 6 slices of bread, layer of cheese over bread, cooked broccoli and diced ham, another layer of cheese.
Put balance of bread on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onions and dry mustard.
Pour on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand, vanilla and chopped strawberries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour 1/3 mixture into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container.
Spoon 1/3 mashed strawberries on top.
Repeat layering; top with strawberry mixture.
Swirl with knife or spatula.
Cover; freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: chicken a la francaise
directions: While rice is cooking, season chicken with salt and pepper. Saute in butter until browned.
Add onions and mushrooms; continue cooking 2 minutes longer.
Stir in sherry (I leave this out), peas and broth.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Dissolve cornstarch in mushroom liquid and stir into chicken mixture.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings and "good"!

title: healthy cakes(muffins)
directions: In a large bowl, mix together oat bran, wheat flour, white flour, oatmeal or bran, raisins, baking soda and baking powder. Add spices as desired.
If using vanilla, add to blender.

title: summer fruit dip
directions: Combine instant pudding with milk.
Add sour cream; mix well, then add pineapple.
Garnish with strawberries.
Chill 2 hours. Serve with savory watermelon, fresh strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew or grapes.

title: armagh pie casserole
directions: Fry sausage slowly until brown; drain and put in 8-inch cake pan or casserole dish.
Fry apples and onions in sausage fat. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Brown flour in remaining fat with apples and onions.
Add seasonings and stock and stir until thickened.
Pour over sausage.
Mix lightly with fork.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° in oven until potatoes are brown. Serves 4.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Boil ingredients for 10 minutes and pour into pie crust.
Cut a circle in the center of the top pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until crust is brown.

title: stuffed-cabbage soup
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart pot over medium heat. Add beef. Saut until browned, about 6 minutes. Add cole slaw mix and onion. Cook, covered, 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, beef broth, water, brown sugar, lemon juice and salt. Bring to boiling. Add rice. Reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until beef and rice are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: elephant stew(a recipe for a large gathering)
directions: Cut up elephant into bite sized pieces, discarding feet. (This takes approximately 2 1/2 months, so allow plenty of time.) Cook in gravy over kerosene fire at 685° until done.
This recipe will serve 600.
If more are expected, add the rabbit.
Do this as a last resort, as most people do not like to find a hare in their stew.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix together.
Brush on ham before cooking and then again during cooking.
Yummy!

title: spinach pasta with cream, nuts and basil
directions: Have all ingredients ready as listed.
Turn cooked pasta into deep heated serving dish.
Add butter in chunks, cream and basil; toss.
Add fresh pepper.
Add nuts and cheese; toss again.
Serve immediately.

title: mother's brownies
directions: Melt together chocolate and shortening. Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, then chocolate mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients; add gradually to chocolate.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.

title: mock oyster stew
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, place eggplant, water and butter. Cook over medium heat until eggplant is soft, about 15 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn to low and heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple with juice. Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread dry cake mix on top (do not mix). Melt butter and pour on top of cake mix. Spread coconut on top, then add nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no apologies meat loaf
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter over moderate heat.
Add the onion, peppers, celery and thyme; reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, stirring once or twice, until vegetables are very soft, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: spicy glazed spareribs
directions: In large, shallow pan, bake spareribs, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.

title: spanish rice mexican-style
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Saute onion and add salsa. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water.
Heat and add rice and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Turn off heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix everything together and serve.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar, egg, chocolate, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop dough by round teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until almost no imprint.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Next melt butter.
Dip chicken in milk, then cornmeal mixture.
Put in baking pan; drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Put cheese in medium size bowl.
Mix in dry Jell-O and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail last.
Put in mold and chill.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, tomatoes, onions and beans.
When ready to serve, add cheese, Fritos and dressing; mix well.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and pineapple. Refrigerate overnight (covered).
Drain this the next day and add whipped cream, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: fruit and honey bars
directions: In medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over juice. Let stand 1 minute, stir over low heat untili gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in honey; then remaining ingredients.
Turn into 8 or 9-inch baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into bars.
Yields about 2 dozen bars.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix together well.
Store in airtight containers.
Use 2 to 4 teaspoons mix to 1 mug of boiling water.
Makes great gifts, too. Put in decorative jar or tin with instructions.

title: corn pone
directions: Add all dry ingredients, cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Place in two round greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked cocktail
directions: Mix well. Pour into greased pan 9 x 9. Cover with 1/2 c brown sugar and about 1/2 c. nutmeats. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: fairy bread
directions: Butter bread and generously sprinkle with rainbow sprinkles. Cut into quarters (triangles) and serve.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
To serve warm, microwave a few minutes until heated or bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: eggplant tomato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick oil spray.
Arrange eggplant on cookie sheet and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over eggplant.
Layer one slice of tomato on each eggplant round.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press into bottom of ungreased square (8 x 8 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour over hot crust. Bake until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center, for about 25 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pat sajak's wedding cake
directions: Beat sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add whipping cream last; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix 1 cup orange juice and 1 cup sugar; bring to a boil and let thicken slightly and pour over hot cake.

title: corn dogs(regular or mini)
directions: You may use either fresh or stale bread.
Cut bread into small cubes, put them in a pan and sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder or leave them plain.
Put them in the oven at 250° for approximately 20 minutes. Turn the oven off and leave the croutons in the oven for another hour or so.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Place muscadines in pot; cover with cold water and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until mushy.
Run through ricer to remove seeds and some of the hulls.
Mix all ingredients with muscadine mush.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell; cover with another pie shell.
Cut three or four slits in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° for 30 minutes more.

title: doris' chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat in a heavy pan.
Stir in 1/3 sugar at a time.
Add salt and stir in milk a little at a time cook over low heat for 7 - 8
minutes, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Use on ice cream or cake.
Store in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas in graham cracker crusts.
Whip cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Pour over bananas.
Add blueberry pie filling. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Dice and brown onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: pizza burgers
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef and green pepper until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in pizza sauce, pepperoni, mushrooms and oregano.
Cook, uncovered, about 1 minute or until heated through.
Spoon mixture onto lettuce lined buns.
Top with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: banana pie
directions: Slice bananas and place in a deep baked pie shell.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, sugar, flour, vanilla and oleo.
Cook until thick.
Spread over bananas.
Beat whites of two eggs thoroughly with a pinch of baking powder.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until smooth and glossy.
Spread over pie.
Brown to a golden brown at 350°.

title: white chili
directions: Cook onion in oil until transparent.
Add all of remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: paul's hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients to paste with buttermilk.
Heat oil in large pot to 325°.
Drop paste by tablespoon into hot grease and cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels to absorb grease. Enjoy with your catfish.

title: molasses blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl mix well the sugar, molasses, oil and hot water.
Stir in baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add flour and blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: anise pizzelles
directions: Preheat 5-inch Pizzelle Iron according to manufacturer's directions.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, at low speed, beat all ingredients until well blended.
Spoon a heaping tablespoonful of mixture onto center of Pizzelle Iron (or use amount recommended by manufacturer), cover and bake until golden brown, about 30 seconds.
Lift cover, carefully lift Pizzelle with small knife. Place on wire rack to cool.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: stroganoff meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soup, sour cream and rice/noodles.
Form meat mixture into approximately 24 balls. Place in 10-inch shallow baking dish.
Pour soup over balls.
Bake 35 minutes in preheated oven.
Blend in sour cream and serve over rice/noodles.

title: variations on a potato theme
directions: Melt butter, saute onion and garlic.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour and stir until bubbly.
Add milk and stir until sauce thickens.
Add potatoes and seasonings.
Turn into greased pan and bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: apple goodies
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place apples in pan. Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly over apples.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave spicy turkey roast
directions: Tips:
Turkey cooked in the microwave is very juicy, but don't overcook it.
Pour the brown juices, which accumulate in the bottom of the microwave-safe roasting pan, over the sliced meat before serving.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles.
Pour sauce on bottom of baking dish.
Layer noodles, spaghetti sauce, sour cream, Ricotta cheese and shredded cheese.
Top with grated cheese and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbling.
Let set and reheat just prior to serving.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mash banana.
Blend in egg, milk, sweetener and shortening. Mix soda, salt and flour and add to mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork in a crisscross motion.
Bake 5 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: candy apple pie
directions: Place sliced apples mixed with lemon juice in pie crust. Mix flour, sugar, and nutmeg. Spread over apples. Dot with oleo. Sprinkle with red hots. Lay second layer of pie crust over top. Crimp edges to seal; cut slits in top. Bake 50 min. at 350°.

title: strawberry cheesecake(low-fat and cholesterol)
directions: Coat the bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray; sprinkle with crumbs and set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cottage cheese and cream cheese product and process until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, vanilla and whole eggs; process until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl; set aside.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently stir one-fourth of egg white mixture into cheese mixture.
Gently fold in remaining egg white mixture. Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Remove pan from oven.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat
dates
in 1 cup water.
Blend 1 cup cashews in 1 cup

title: ranch style eggs
directions: In small skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Holding tortillas with tongs, dip one at a time in hot oil for 10 seconds, or until limp.
Line a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas; keep warm.
In same skillet, cook the onion and garlic until tender but not brown (add more oil if necessary).
Stir in tomatoes, green chili peppers and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Spoon over tortillas.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan with cooking spray.
Heat pan over medium-high heat.
Cook rice in pan abut 5 minutes or until light brown, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add onions, wine, thyme and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes or until liquid has evaporated.
Stir in 1 cup of broth and cook until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 cup of broth and cook until absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken, peas and last of the broth.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Continue to stir occasionally to keep rice from sticking; let it cook on low until liquid is gone, chicken is tender and rice is done.

title: p.t.a.  casserole
directions: Brown meat; pour off grease.
Add everything into casserole. Just fold together; don't whip.
Bake at 350° for at least 1/2 hour.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after adding each egg.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk and water.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.
Start in a cold oven.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt.
In a cup, beat egg, vinegar and cold water; pour over flour mixture and stir.
Roll into pie crust.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix above ingredients together thoroughly.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Check in 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 small or 2 medium or 1 large loaf.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch plastic flower pot, plastic or silk flowers and a hand trowel.

title: grandma podewels' icebox cake
directions: Layer crushed or whole vanilla wafers in bottom of an 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan lined with foil (foil should be extended out over edge of pan for easy removal).
Cream oleo until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and mix well. Combine pineapple and oleo mixture and layer alternately with vanilla wafers ending up with the wafers.
Press lightly with a spoon and chill in refrigerator 24 hours (or freeze).
Garnish with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Slice to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and chill in ice water overnight.
Pack in jars with dill and garlic.
Separate pods of garlic and put 3 pieces of garlic and flowertop and leaf of dill into 1 quart jar.
Bring to boiling point, but do not boil, the water, salt and vinegar.
Pour mixture over cucumbers; seal at once.
Cures in 6 to 8 weeks. Enough for about 8 quarts.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, onion and egg.
Shape into twenty 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven until done and light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix 1/3 cup milk, nutmeg and soup.
Add drained meatballs.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through. Yields 4 servings.
Serve with noodles.

title: fool proof chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk and dash of salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread on foil lined pan.
Chill for 2 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.
(Makes 2 pounds.)

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir quickly and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Serve after cooling 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta squash medley
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion; stir briefly. Add squash and pepper; cook for 2 to 3 minutes until crisp-tender. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables and toss until cheese melts.
Serve on spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: salmon potato salad
directions: Drain salmon, saving juice.
Flake salmon; mix with potatoes, green onions, cucumber, celery, parsley and herb.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper and saved salmon juice.
Pour over salmon-potato mixture; mix gently but well.
Pack salad into 10-cup mold and chill.
When ready to serve, unmold and garnish with tomatoes and sprays of parsley.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mixed salad medley
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook sugar, vinegar, water, mustard and flour until thick (2 or 3 minutes).
Cool.
Pour over vegetables and marinate at least 24 hours.
Stir a couple times.
Can be made 4 days ahead.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini until dry.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add apricot Jell-O.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Two to four days before serving:

In a large bowl, combine vinegar, wine, water, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon peppercorns, bay leaves, 3 onions, 12 cloves, 1 teaspoon mustard seed and 2 teaspoons salt. Set meat in marinade, cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 days, depending on degree of sourness desired.
Turn meat each day.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Crust: Mix flour and margarine. Put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Let cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Do not pour out the grease.
Put cheese in and let melt.
Remove from heat.
Add Bisquick.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into small balls.
Cook at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill large salad bowl half full of shredded lettuce.
Add the next four ingredients in layers.
Sprinkle the sugar over the mayonnaise.
Add a layer of cheese, topped with a layer of bacon bits.
Don't mix.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown roast in oven on both sides.
Cover and cook until tender.
Take out and slice in thin slices.
Add some water to beef drippings and spices.
Put sliced beef back in juice.
Cover. Cook at 250° about 2 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: fudge pie
directions: Dump all ingredients (except pie shell) into a bowl and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top chilled pie with Dream Whip, if desired.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine scalded sour cream, sugar and butter and salt; mix well.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture, then eggs.
Gradually stir in flour (dough will be soft).
Cover tightly; chill overnight.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Turn each portion out on a heavily floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll each into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread 1/4 filling over each rectangle, leaving a 1/2-inch margin around edges.
Carefully roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning at long side.
Firmly pinch edges and ends to seal.
Place rolls, seam side down, on greased baking sheets.
Make 6 equally spaced x-shaped cuts across top of each loaf.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread with glaze while warm.
Yields 4 (12-inch) loaves.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Fry hamburger
and
onion
until brown.
Drain off fat. Add the
remaining
ingredients and mix well.
Brown hamburger buns under
broiler,
then
add	hamburger mixture; cover with Provolone cheese and return to broiler until melted.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
This makes large amount for a party.
For family use; freeze in 3 or 4 containers and use 1 at a time.
Unused portions can be refrozen.

title: friendship fruitcake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
In a very large container, mix sugar, salt, spices and crumbs.
Beat eggs and milk and add to the dry mixture.
Add fruits and nuts, mixing well. Spoon into a tube pan completely lined with aluminum foil and greased.
Decorate the top with whole candied pineapple slices and candied cherries.
Cover with foil tightly and bake in 225° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil from the top for the last 30 minutes of baking.
Cool completely in the pan.
Remove from pan, wrap in foil and store in the refrigerator.
This cake improves with age so it is best to make it in September or October.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix oatmeal, 1 cup white sugar, flour and melted oleo.
Save 1 cup for topping and press remaining into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Cook until clear and thick water, 1 cup white sugar and cornstarch.
Add fresh or frozen blueberries.
Spread over base in pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: polynesian pork canton
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil until it starts to smoke.
Add pork, cut into 1/8-inch strips.
Stir quickly over high heat until pork is cooked, about 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender but crisp, about 6 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; stir in quickly.
Cook, stirring, until mixture bubbles and thickens. Season to taste with salt.
Serve with hot rice.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Dice and cook the potatoes in salt water.
Add butter, pepper and onion.
When potatoes are tender, add milk.
Let come to a boil.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Mix thoroughly; let stand overnight in cool place.
In morning, cook 1/2 hour over medium heat, stirring as needed.
Put in jars and seal.

title: "mock" field's special sandwich
directions: Mix mayonnaise and barbecue sauce together well.
Cut one slice rye bread in half.
Place full slice in center of plate and 1/2 slices on either side.
Spread dressing on bread.

title: just "peachy" cobbler
directions: In a bowl mix peaches, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
In a deep Corning Ware dish, melt butter.
In a bowl mix flour, 1 cup sugar, buttermilk and vanilla and pour into butter.
Spoon in peaches and juice.
Bake at 425°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: american rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour hot milk in bowl.
Add butter.
Mix yeast and lukewarm water now, while milk mixture cools.
Let milk mixture cool to lukewarm, then add salt, sugar, eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir well.
Add flour, about two cups at a time.
Mix well and spoon until dough is sticky thick and ready to knead. Knead and place dough in buttered bowl by turning butter side of dough up.
Let rise about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Punch dough down and roll into desired shape.
Place in buttered pans.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Put cheese, 1 pepper and onions through a grinder.
Add liquids and red pepper.
Shape into a ball, then roll on wax paper in paprika and finely chopped pecans.
Put in refrigerator to set. Decorate with a jalapeno pepper, cut in strips lengthwise.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar together.
Set aside.
Place egg whites, cream of tartar and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Gradually add sugar (about 2 tablespoons at a time). Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Fold in vanilla and almond extract.
Add gradually flour-powdered sugar mixture over meringue.
Fold in gently just until the flour-powdered sugar mixture disappears.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Gently cut through batter with knife.
Bake at 375° until top springs back when lightly touched.
Invert on a funnel.
Let hang until cool, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, water chestnuts, soup and French fried onion rings together.
Put
crushed
crackers
over top.	Pour butter over and cook in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: Place
the pie filling in an 8-inch
square baking dish and pour cake mix over pie filling.
Cut butter in thin slices and place over cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until it thickens and bubbles. Remove sauce from heat.

title: marcia's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in covered dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or longer at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients well, then add flour.
Mix well.
Roll dough balls to the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet and crisscross with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° until bottom of cookies are just lightly browned or about 9 minutes.
Leave on sheets for 1 minute, then transfer to wax paper to set up and cool.
Cookie should be soft and chewy without falling apart.

title: apple with hay
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over low heat.
Add sugar.
Turn up heat to high and cook, stirring occasionally until mixture forms a light brown syrup.
Add apples to syrup and brown on each side, turning only once.
When apples are a light brown, remove them to an oven-proof pan and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Bake apples about 8 minutes until glazed and heated through.

title: no fat chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Set aside.
Whisk together remaining ingredients.
Whisk into dry ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch square or oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip lite.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except for boiled eggs.
Press 1/2 of the mixture in microwave-safe loaf pan, then insert boiled eggs, lining the middle of loaf.
Now, pat remainder of meat mixture on top of the eggs, covering lower half of mixture and eggs completely.
Microwave on "High" for 16 to 20 minutes, until done.
You may wish to place slices of Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese on top during last 2 minutes of cooking.

title: chocolate cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Melt chips in double boiler. Mix with cream cheese.
Stir in nuts.
Chill and shape into balls. Roll in nuts.
May serve with butter cookies or other cookies of choice.

title: easy apple betty
directions: Mix sliced apples and pineapple together.
Add white and brown sugars.
Place mixture into long, flat baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of fruits evenly.
Slice margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: holiday blue cheese spread
directions: Beat together cheeses until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold oranges, reserving a few to garnish.
Chill until set, at least one hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mix cheese with bread crumbs.
Melt butter on cookie sheet at 400°.
Add salt, garlic powder and 1/2 of parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Arrange shrimp in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp over and sprinkle with bread crumbs mixed with lemon juice.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Cook bacon in 2 quarts of water until done.
Add peas and salt.
Cook 30 minutes or until peas are tender.
Add rice and boil 15 to 18 minutes longer.
Lift out bacon and set aside.
Drain peas and rice thoroughly, then place in warm oven for a few minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Serve with bacon on top.

title: griddlecakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, along with shortening, mixing just until flour is dampened.
Add milk as desired for thinner cakes (batter will be lumpy).
Cook on hot greased griddle.
Yields 10 to 12 cakes.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and juice from pineapple.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 350°.
Drain meatballs; place on chafing dish.

title: tuna fettucine
directions: Bring large pot of water to a boil.
Cook broccoli until crisp-tender, remove with slotted spoon and place in serving bowl. Add fettucine to same pot of boiling water and cook until tender. Drain and add to broccoli.
Mix in tuna.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook in same pot, stirring until sauce is smooth and heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over pasta and toss.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Keep in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: chicken vegetable casserole(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients to form a sauce.
Set aside. Microwave mixed vegetables in a casserole dish for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Drain.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 of vegetables, chicken, sauce and cheese; repeat.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Reduce power to 50% and microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.
Rotate heated mixture halfway during cooking time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese and Jell-O in the cup boiling water with beater.
Mix in other ingredients.
Chill.

title: yummy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and tear into small pieces. Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and seasonings. Place in casserole dish. Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine. Sprinkle cracker mixture over top and bake at 350° until golden and bubbly.

title: mom's bake beans
directions: Saute onions and bacon chunks until brown.
Pour it into 1 gallon casserole dish along with drippings and all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: leila brandon's seasoned rice
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stand in warm place for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork and serve.
A Jamaican dish.
Serves 6.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl by hand, cream together margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Melt chocolate square and vanilla until blended.
Reduce speed; stir in potatoes and mix well.
Put on waxed paper.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk or sour milk, blending well after each addition.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans (or one 9-inch tube pan).
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sauce for conch fritters
directions: Mix and serve with conch fritters.

title: sweet valentine heart
directions: Place gelatin in blender.
Pour boiling water over it.
Let stand for 1 minute, then blend at high speed for 1 minute until gelatin dissolves.
Add cream, sugar and vanilla.
Blend at medium speed.
Add Ricotta, a little at a time and blend.
Cut cream cheese in 1-inch cubes, add a few at a time while blending.
When smooth pour in mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold.
Serves 8.

title: microwave meringues
directions: Put the egg white into a 1.75 litre (3-pint) mixing bowl and beat until frothy.
Gradually work in the icing sugar and mix to give a really stiff fondant.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Make a smooth paste of 1/2 cup vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric and cornstarch.
Simmer 3 minutes and seal in hot jars.

title: low-fat ice cream
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add evaporated milk. Add enough milk to mix thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream freezer, adding enough milk to fill freezer.
Use any flavor pudding desired.
Add fresh fruit if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, gelatin, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan. Stir in boiling water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange whole strawberries on top and chill several hours.
Top with whipped topping.

title: brittany beef en casserole
directions: Cook bacon in heavy frying pan until brown.
Remove from pan and add cloves, garlic and beef cubes rolled in flour.
Brown.
Add consomme, wine and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Put in baking dish with carrots, peppercorns, bay leaves and cut bacon.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
When cooked add 1 jar of onions.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Spread in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots. Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add slightly beaten eggs and beat well.
Add sour cream and vanilla while continuing to beat. Blend thoroughly.
Spread half of dough in greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 of topping over it.
Spread remaining mixture into pan. Sprinkle rest of topping on.
Pour melted butter over top (1/4 cup).
I slice in apple and put in middle of cake.
Makes it moist.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese chutney spread
directions: Pour chutney over the blocks of cream cheese.
Top with bacon.

title: marinated steak(lo-fat)
directions: Place steak in baking dish and cover with marinade made from rest of the ingredients.
Turn to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat broiler. Remove steak and pat dry. Sprinkle freshly ground pepper on steak.
Broil 4 to 6-inches from broiler 4 to 7 minutes on a side.
Slice thinly across the grain.

title: new potatoes and garlic baked in parchment
directions: You will need 1 sheet of baking parchment paper, approximately 11 x 16-inches.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 325° and bake for another 45 minutes.

title: peach glace pie(microwave)
directions: In a 4 cup measure, stir together sugar, cornstarch, orange peel and nutmeg.
Add peach nectar; mix well.
Cook, uncovered, on 100% power for 4 to 6 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring each minute until mixture starts to thicken,
then every 30 seconds until bubbly.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 30 seconds more.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Arrange peaches in cooled pie shell.
Pour liquid mixture evenly over fruit.
Chill for 2 hours.
Dollop with whipped cream.
Garnish with strawberry.
Serves eight.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup of water in 4-cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 3 minutes, stir thoroughly.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until a small amount of syrup dropped in cold water forms a hard ball.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites in a large bowl with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
When syrup is ready, pour in a very thin slow stream into egg whites.
Beat constantly with mixer on high.
Add vanilla and beat 6 to 8 minutes, or until mixture is stiff and loses its shine.
Fold in nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. When cool, store in tight container.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandma donut holes
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Drop in hot oil.
Deep fry on medium high until brown, then roll each one in sugar.

title: zesty turkey wrap
directions: Combine turkey, onions and dressing in a medium bowl.
Place lettuce leaves on one edge of each tortilla.
Divide turkey mixture among tortillas, place on lettuce.
Roll to wrap.
If using pita pockets, line each pocket with lettuce and add turkey.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and let thicken.
Mix together all other ingredients and stir into jello.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add raisins, cabbage and apples.
Tie pickling spices in wet piece of cheesecloth.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook over low heat for about 45 minutes.
Mix sugar and vinegar; stir into cabbage.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked spaghetti dish
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and Italian seasoning. Simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift salt, soda and flour together.
Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add unbeaten egg; mix well.
Add bananas and the flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Put in a greased loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and sweet potatoes
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Cover with onion slices.
Add 3/4 cup apple juice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In bowl, mix flour, allspice and 1/4 cup apple juice.
Place sweet potatoes around chops in pan.
Pour mixture over all.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Dip in egg; roll in grated Swiss cheese.
Roll in Italian bread crumbs or Pepperidge Farm seasoned bread crumbs.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes on each side.
The longer the chicken is baked at a low temperature, the more tender they will be.

title: strawberry cream delight
directions: Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish and let jell.
Add and spread over 1 cup sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture and let jell.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onion.
Separate into rings.
Cover with milk and soak for about 2 hours.
Pour pancake or biscuit mix into bag; shake rings in bags.
Deep fat fry.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Cut dates into small pieces and put into mixing bowl.
Put soda and butter over dates, then pour hot water over this and let stand for 10 minutes.
Then, mix in other ingredients.
Pour into baking pan and bake 1 hour in 375° oven or until done.

title: lime kool-aid jello punch
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 1 quart water.
Mix with jello and add pineapple juice.
Place in refrigerator.
Just before serving, mix with ginger ale.
This is a "fun" drink for a teenage party.
Lime sherbet can be floated in punch bowl with green or red cherries for decoration.
Makes 36 servings.

title: nana's easy and good baked chicken
directions: Put Rice Krispies in blender.
Melt oleo; dip chicken in melted oleo, then into Rice Krispies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sally jo's lemon dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts; press into an 8
x 11-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until light brown. Let cool.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Let rise to double, then roll out 1/3-inch thick; cut and let rise until very light (30 to 40 minutes).
Leave uncovered so crust will form.
Fry in deep hot fat at 375°.

title: apple crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix well remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm and ice cream may be served with apples.

title: fudge or frosting
directions: Place in thick bottom pan the sugar, milk and marshmallows. Boil for 6 minutes on medium high heat, stirring constantly.
Place in bowl:
nuts, oleo, vanilla, salt and chips.
Pour marshmallows over nut mixture and stir well.
Pour into greased plate and cool until it can be cut.
Boil only 3 minutes for frosting.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Place in a long shallow pan that has
been
greased
and
floured.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven
until
an
inserted toothpick can be removed clean. May be glazed.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and yeast. In a saucepan, heat milk, 1/4 cup sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) and butter is almost melted.
Stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture; add eggs.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: easy elegant shrimp stroganoff
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions; drain.

title: holiday cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar until very light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each addition. Fold in flour, vanilla and candied fruit. Line a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan with aluminum foil. Pour in batter, bake at 325° for one hour and 45 minutes. Frost with confectioners sugar icing. Decorate with candied fruit.

title: eggless, butterless, milkless cake
directions: Boil raisins, sugar, coffee, salt and shortening for five minutes; cool.
Sift together dry ingredients three times and add to mixture.
Bake in two loaf pans or one tube pan at 275° for 90 to 105 minutes.

title: seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except almonds or paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: bow ties and cabbage
directions: In large frying pan, melt margarine and saute cabbage and onion until soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Mix with cabbage; serve.

title: sausage stars
directions: Lightly oil both sides of won ton wrappers and press into muffin pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 5 minutes). Remove from pan and place on baking sheet. Combine all the ingredients. Fill shells with mixture and bake on baking sheet for 5 minutes or until bubbly.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease lightly a 9-inch deep pan. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom of pan.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and mix at high speed for 1 minute.
Pour in pan.
Bake until golden brown or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mom's chicken and rice
directions: Combine soups and rice in crock-pot. Cover with chicken. Cover pot and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rick's chili - hot
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft and tender.
Add beef, cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, paste, water/wine and seasonings. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat and simmer for a few hours. Add rinsed kidney beans last 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
When cool, peel and dice.
Fry bacon very crispy and crumble over diced potatoes with chopped onion and parsley flakes.
Leave half the bacon grease in frying pan and add vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 or 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, to dissolve sugar.
Test for proper sweet and sour taste.
Add more vinegar or sugar, if needed.
Pour over potatoes and stir from the bottom to be sure the vinegar mixture soaks the potatoes well.
Keep at room temperature for best taste.
If refrigeration is needed, remove from the refrigerator at least 1 hour and stir good before serving.

title: colorful rice confetti
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray and heat until hot.
Add zucchini and onion; saute until crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer approximately 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings (about 84 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: sauced smokies
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients in crock-pot; mix.
Cook on high until bubbly.
Turn on low for another 30 minutes.
Serve.
Great at potlucks.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the peanut butter, sugar and cream cheese. Stir in whipped cream and vanilla; pour into crust.
Chill 4 to 5 hours, or until well set.
Top with Cool Whip; chill again for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, vanilla and sugars.
Add egg. Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk gradually and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in a small amount into the egg yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook for another 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool slightly.
Slice the bananas into the baked pastry shell. Pour filling over.
Cool before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: saucy vegetables
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Heat cheese and milk until smooth. Add vegetables and reheat.
Top with onions and serve.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cheese, salt and pepper. Place 3 lasagna noodles in greased pan.
Add half of potatoes. Top with 3 lasagna noodles.
Repeat with remaining potatoes and noodles.
Saute onion in butter and pour over casserole.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken chili dip
directions: Microwave all ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable bowl on High 6 to 8 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring every 3 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers, tortilla chips or assorted cut up vegetables.

title: scallops in white wine
directions: Simmer the scallops, wine, shallots and parsley in a saucepan for 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: fruit cake, kentucky bourbon
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients together.
Mix fruit, marmalade and nuts in a large bowl.
Add 1 cup of dry ingredients to egg and sugar mix, alternating with bourbon.
Stir in fruit mix.
Bake in greased and papered 10-inch pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cool.
Wrap in cloth dampened with bourbon.
Place in airtight container along with apple slices.
Allow cake to ripen before cutting, about 1 month.
Yields 8 pounds.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant; cut in 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Brown the meats together with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain mixture; add eggplant and 1/4 cup corn flake crumbs.
Blend well.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with a layer of grated cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: To juice (about 1/2 cup) and 1 tablespoon grated rind of orange, add oil and enough hot water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add to sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in honey and egg.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; invert on wire rack.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugars.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Combine sour cream and Cool
Whip.
Add drained fruits.
Pour dry jello over mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve as needed.
Will keep a number of days.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring until bubbly.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken, ham, rice, celery, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and paprika and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy salad surprise
directions: In a large bowl, combine the vegetables. Toss to coat.

title: lasagne
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in skillet.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
In blender, mix tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce mix.
Pour sauce into large saucepan; add meat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until ready to assemble lasagne.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Cut onion and celery into casserole dish.
Add mushrooms, stuffing and both cans of soup; mix well.
Pick chicken off bone and add to casserole dish; mix well.
Salt to taste.
Put in oven at 400° until brown.
Delicious hot or cold.

title: chicken-cheese spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken in oil until done (not brown).
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Add chicken soup and chicken broth.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Cook spaghetti (drained).
Add chicken mixture to spaghetti and cook a few minutes.
Can eat this way or put in casserole dish; top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Good!

title: orange cottage cheese dressing
directions: Blend at high speed until creamy smooth.
Makes 1 cup.
Pour over salad.
Serve with bread pudding, etc.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour chili mix into 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with corn bread mixture (thin if needed).
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Measure and sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add melted butter or margarine, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth. Fold in nuts.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and 2 sticks melted butter.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: pineapple walnut dessert
directions: Spread pineapple and juice evenly on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of pineapple; spread evenly with fork.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Dribble melted butter over nuts, covering all the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until light brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Make crisscross marks on top of cookie with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: black-eyed pea corn bread
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Add onion and peppers. Set aside. Mix corn meal, flour, salt, soda, buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn together. Add first mixture and mix together well. Add cheese and peas; mix well. Pour into oblong pan that has been greased well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffing
directions: Place bread in large bowl; add egg.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add that to bread mixture.
Add seasoning.
Then add milk. Form into a ball.
If it is too moist, add more bread.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spray muffin pans with a vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients together except pecans; mix well.
Add pecans and bake for 45 minutes or until the pies are brown. Yields 6 pies.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Dissolve raspberry, lime and orange gelatins, each in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) square pans; chill until firm.
Blend pineapple juice, water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add lemon gelatin; stir until dissolved. Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg white. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut pans of gelatin into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fold into lemon gelatin mixture.
Pour into 9-inch tube or form pan; chill until firm.
Unmold and frost with remaining Cool Whip flavored with vanilla.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts, if desired.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Yields 12 servings.
A party dessert; gelatin colors can be changed to holiday colors for something different!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls. Bake on cookie sheet for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and sift together all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, pumpkin and eggs.
Beat with mixer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: brown sugar pound cake(with caramel rum sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugars until very light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine dry ingredients, then add to batter alternately with milk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture. Add vanilla. Fill prepared pan and bake for 1 hour and 35-40 min or until toothpick inserted in center of
cake comes out clean. Cool cake completely, then remove from pan. To serve drizzle with Rum Sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew hen until tender and remove from stock.
When cold, skin, bone and cut up.
Cook spaghetti in stock until tender.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: In 13 x 9-inch cake pan, melt butter or margarine with brown sugar until butter or margarine is melted and sugar dissolved. Remove from heat.
Immediately toss pretzels in pan; spread evenly and bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove cool to lukewarm. Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool and add strawberries.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth, then beat in carton of Cool Whip slowly.
Spread on evenly over pretzels, seal edge all around pan with this.
Carefully spread (pour) jello mixture over cream layer.
Refrigerate until jello is set, about 1 hour or longer. Cut into squares.

title: pea salad
directions: Be sure to have peas chilled in a bowl before combining it with other ingredients.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and chill.
Mix the cheese to pea mixture and serve.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Mix the ketchup and water with barbecue sauce.
Put wieners in crock-pot.
Pour sauce over and cook until wieners are done, about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all except pecans.
Chill, form a ball, and roll in crushed pecans.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Sift flour once measured; add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Add lemon and orange rind to butter and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add flour with water. Bake in two layers in moderate oven.
Spread orange coconut filling between layers and on the top.
Frost cake completely with seven minute frosting.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 2 packages chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: scrumptious zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender; saute carrots and onions in butter until limp. Add soup and cream; mix in 3/4 of croutons (gently). Pour into a greased casserole. In 2 tablespoons of butter, put the remaining croutons; toss until well coated. Sprinkle on top of casserole; bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: soft shelled crabs
directions: Salt and pepper each crab.
Roll each crab in the flour and shake off excess.
Place in heated skillet of medium-hot fat. Cook on medium heat until golden brown.

title: skillet upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Heat an 11-inch electric skillet to 220°.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Arrange 9 slices of pineapple or other fruit in bottom of skillet.
If desired, add maraschino cherries and nuts.
Turn skillet to 260° and pour in prepared cake mix.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes with air vent on skillet lid closed tightly.
Don't peek.
When done, turn out on suitable plate.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In 10-inch
skillet,
cook squash, onion and oleo until tender (about
minutes).
Stir
in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl,
blend
eggs
and
cheese.
Stir
in vegetable mixture. Separate
crescent
rolls
into 8 triangles (this is enough for two pies).
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie plates. Press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable
mixture
into crust.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: kolbassi - low-fat
directions: Boil potatoes and carrots until almost done. Brown kolbassi, onion and pepper until onion is transparent. Drain potatoes and carrots. Add to the meat and cook about 15 minutes.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Fry bacon until very crispy; break in 1 inch pieces; set aside.
Combine ketchup, sugar, vinegar and mustard; add beans, bacon and ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: big mac
directions: From Main Street, get on Highway 92 Bridge.
Cross tracks going toward I-75.
When Highway 92 makes 90° turn at traffic light, take a left and enter McDonald's parking lot.
Drive up and order to your heart's content!

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook uncovered in double boiler, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Cover bottom of casserole with a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of bananas.
Spread about 1/4 pudding mixture on top.
Repeat vanilla wafers and bananas.
Add remaining pudding mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff, add 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on top and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook pasta per directions; drain.
In bowl, blend together soup, milk, mayo and mustard.
Stir in cheese and chicken. Gently fold in pasta.
Put in large casserole.
Combine crumbs, melted butter and paprika.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a bundt pan and smooth out the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
This cake requires no frosting, but you can lightly dust it with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat together the next 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.
Enjoy!

title: good beef stew
directions: In baking dish with tight fitting lid, combine all of the ingredients.
Do not brown the meat.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Don't hurry the stew, as the long cooking time and slow oven are the key to its success.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and crackers, in large bowl.
If necessary, add salad dressing to hold together.
Roll in pecan pieces and shape into ball.
Place on serving tray and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until well blended.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 3 or 4 times. Roll dough into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage over dough, leaving 1/2-inch margin on all sides.
Carefully roll dough lengthwise jellyroll fashion, seal.
Cover and refrigerate at least an hour.
Slice 1/4-inch slices; arrange over baking sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cajun okra
directions: You can use this same method to cook any kind of field peas, such as black-eyed or crowder; cream peas of any kind, but not English peas.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix with a fork until like oatmeal.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Pour into 1 (9 x 13-inch) or small or 3 (9-inch) pie shells.
Top with the one cup you set aside.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Check after 45 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Put hamburg in skillet and cook until redness disappears; then add macaroni.
Put tomatoes over and simmer until done.
Makes a large casserole.
May also add cheese from Kraft dinner.

title: chicken noodle supreme
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions for 4 minutes. Drain.
Mix chicken, ham or tuna, soup, milk, cheese, onion and parsley in bowl until well blended.
Add noodles and toss.
Salt to taste.
Turn mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt in double boiler and serve with doritos.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix in the order as given.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding cornbread last.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes (until the top is lightly brown).

title: chicken divan
directions: Place thawed broccoli in baking pan.
Place uncooked chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon, curry powder and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Place cheese on top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: greek chicken
directions: Combine garlic powder, olive oil, oregano, onion, lemon juice and salt.
Marinate chicken pieces in mixture overnight.
Melt butter in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pina colada fruit salad
directions: Combine coconut, yogurt, pineapple juice and rum extract in a small glass bowl.
Stir to blend.
Fold in fresh or canned fruits just before serving.
Yield: 8 servings (4 cups).
Serving Size: 1/2 cup.
Per serving:
Calories: 75, Fat: 1 g, Sodium: 29 mg. Exchanges per serving: 1 fruit.

title: microwave easy mexican meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine beef, egg and seasoning mix. Shape into 48 (1-inch) balls.
Put 12 beef balls in circle on paper plate.
Cover plate with wax paper.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after one minute.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, water and cinnamon in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Slice into pan and mix.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples; pat smooth.
Bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes, until apples are tender and crust nicely browned.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix together.
Place in bowl or pan that can go into oven. Set bowl in pan or skillet of water and bake in oven until knife stuck in the middle comes out clean.

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Shred half the cheese and mix in lentil mixture.
Put in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours; stir twice. Uncover casserole and top with strips of cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lo-cal jam
directions: Put fruit puree in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice.
Stir, stir, stir! Cool and refrigerate until set.

title: crepes
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add salt and vanilla.
Slowly add flour and beat by hand.
Using a small frying pan put in enough oil that would cover crepe.
Make oil hot.
Pour batter in pan.
Fry lightly; turn and do other side.
You can use syrup or jelly and jam on crepe.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Add chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Mix the next 9 ingredients in a large bowl. Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full with chocolate mix.
