Place a heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese on top of each batter.
Bake in oiled and floured cupcake tins for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini per package directions, drain.
Place in a large bowl.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Crumble Feta cheese and Greek olives on top.
Serve cold.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash, boil, drain, cool and then cut up potatoes, sliced or cubed in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with oil and vinegar.
Toss to mix.
In a small bowl mix all the remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss to coat evenly.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, butter and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Stir.
Pour over popcorn.
Put in pans and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: best banana bread
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Add banana and eggs. Mix well, add flour a little at a time and mix with each addition.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Soften the cream cheese and butter; beat together.
Add the sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and set aside. Prepare the cake-like brownie batter as directed on box.
Pour half the brownie batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour all the cream cheese mixture over the brownie layer.
Spoon the remaining brownie batter in spots over the top.
Swirl the 2 mixtures together with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: In large, preheated pot, saute bacon and 1/2 of the onions, bell pepper, mushrooms and seasonings.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and ketchup.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In preheated skillet, saute remaining vegetables.
Add meats and seasonings; brown thoroughly.
Drain fat in colander; let stand until sauce is done.
Add to sauce; simmer 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture into a long Pyrex dish.
Let congeal.
Spread sour cream over it and pour remaining jello mixture on top.
Congeal.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in 13 x 9 pan. Mix potato soup, sour cream and cheese. Spread over hash browns. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown flour, onion and chopped beef in oil in large skillet. Add tomato juice, salt, brown sugar and dash of pepper.
Add potatoes, string beans and chopped carrots.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: shake 'n bake potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and quarter them.
Put them in a bowl of water to keep them wet.
Place 3 to 4 quarters in the bag of Shake 'n Bake. Shake and coat real well.
Place coated potatoes in a casserole dish.
Continue until all potatoes have been coated.
Place a pat of butter on each potato.
Sprinkle any leftover Shake 'n Bake on top of potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour or until potatoes are done.

title: deep south pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add oil 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add eggs one at a time beating slightly after each addition.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Add the milk and flour alternately, ending with flour.
Pour into a greased tube pan with bottom lined with greased waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: basic meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange in pan (do not touch).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes. Serve with:

title: cherry bars
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla together for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Reserve 1-1/2 cups of batter.
Spread remaining batter into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Spread cherries on top.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over the top of cherries.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: sour cream and onion dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with potato chips or vegetables.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put enough oil in frying pan to coat the bottom.
Add ground meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Cut up onion finely and add to meat.
Cut up celery finely and add to meat.
Cut up green peppers finely and add to meat.
Sprinkle in garlic salt for taste.
Fry until meat loses redness.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce and rinse cans with water.
Add pinch of sugar and bay leaves.
Sprinkle in oregano, basil and a little ketchup.
Simmer slowly all day.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until slightly thickened.
Cool mixture, then combine with the remaining ingredients.
Top with dry roasted peanuts.
Chill before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pat's quickie patties
directions: Shape meat into small patties, adding a few green chilies to each.
Cook to medium done in a large frying pan coated with a smidgen of oil.
Add stewed tomatoes and heat.
Put a slice of cheese on each patty and cover so the cheese melts a little.

title: pea wiggle
directions: Take meat drippings and add 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil; add 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 teaspoon instant coffee (mix first with little water).
Stir until thickens.
This gives your gravy a nice, rich flavor and color.

title: crawfish casserole or shrimp casserole
directions: Cook onions, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add soups, garlic, parsley, green onions, pimento and crawfish.
Heat thoroughly until crawfish are cooked.
Add salt and hot sauce to taste.
Stir in rice and bread crumbs.

title: raspberry cooler(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar and water in 2-quart casserole.
Heat, covered, on full power for 3 to 5 minutes or until sugar is dissolved and water is hot.
Stir halfway through heating time.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: In electric blender, combine all ingredients at low speed; blend until smooth.
Serve with any sliced cold meats.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: hot 'n spicy veggies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; mix well and set aside.
Cut flowerets off of broccoli spears; cut spears into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Set flowerets and spears aside.
Coat a large heavy skillet or wok with oil; add broccoli and carrot. Stir-fry 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: colorful veggie bake
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions; drain. Place half in an ungreased 11 x 7 baking dish. In a small saucepan, combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter; cook and stir over low heat until melted. Pour half over vegetables. Repeat layers.

title: mustard steak
directions: Mix olive oil, wine, scallions and mustard in a small bowl. Place the London broil in a baking pan with the garlic cut into small pieces.
Place the mixture from the small bowl on the meat, top with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marinade for steaks
directions: Scratch the surface of the steaks.
Pour equal amounts of both sauces on steaks, leaving small amount of liquid on steaks.
Put garlic salt on to taste.
Sprinkle with basil.
Let set for 1 hour before cooking.

title: fat boys delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Flour, margarine and pecan pieces; finely chopped. Press in pan, sprinkle with sugar.

title: louisiana beef stew
directions: Add beef to the next 4 ingredients; shake until coated.
Brown in oil.
Add to mixture of remaining ingredients and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, add 6 to 8 carrots, cut in diagonal pieces and 1/2 cup of raisins.

title: jam without sugar
directions: In saucepan, add berries and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil for 1 or 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add Knox dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add sweetener.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: mom's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour; add to eggs.
Add 1 quart milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously.
When mixture coats spoon, remove from heat.
Add mixed Eagle Brand milk and water; add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Strain and chill overnight.
Use peaches, strawberries or bananas (your choice).
Blend each; add to custard mixture and put in freezer.
Using electric churn or freezer, churn until frozen, 15 to 20 minutes.
Use ice and ice cream salt generously.

title: crescent meltaways
directions: In medium bowl, with pastry fork, blend cottage cheese with 1 cup butter.
Sift in flour, then blend until dough forms a ball.

title: glazed bacon
directions: Put the bacon in a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes; drain off the fat.
At this point, before you add the glaze, the bacon should be almost crisp (be sure not to underbake it).

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes:
margarine, brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Take off heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over 8 to 10 quarts of popped corn and nuts (if desired).
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk yeast rolls
directions: Let the milk get room temperature.
Put in yeast and dissolve. Make up your dough; roll out thin.
Cut in biscuits and put melted butter on each and then put another thin biscuit on top. Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 2 servings.

title: hershey's chocolate pie
directions: Dissolve all over hot water, except whipping cream.
Add 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pea soup(from "anderson's" in california)
directions: Cook slowly until peas and vegetables are very soft.
Strain through sieve.
I put soft vegetables in Cuisinart and mix with some of soup and put all back into pot.
If too thick, thin with small can chicken broth.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes; remove and continue on rack.

title: garlic sauce for macaroni
directions: Mix together and pour over macaroni dish.

title: marsha's fan fair vegie casserole
directions: Place vegies in large casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and bell pepper and pour over vegies.
Add 1 cup of cheese.
Put 1/2 cup cheese over top, mix stuffing as directed and place on top of casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Boil noodles about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Meanwhile, mix Spike, broth, water and slice or cube cheese in bowl and microwave until melted. Stir until sauce is creamy.
Do the same on stove top if microwave is not available.
Add sauce to noodles and mix well.
Add salmon and vegetables.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat delight
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add the seasonings with Worcestershire sauce.
Add flour; let bubble until thoroughly combined.
Gradually add milk; stir in beaten egg yolks and crabmeat.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mother's ice cream pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt.
Add to butter mixture and blend well.
Chill 30 to 45 minutes.
Pat into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with ice cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Add onion, if you wish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour.

title: bleu cheese straws
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Blend in flour.
Add poppy seed.
Press through "star" in cookie press or roll in wax paper.
Chill and slice.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Saute onion.
Stir in brown sugar.
Combine barbecue sauce, beans, beef, bacon and seasonings in saucepan.
Stir in onion mixture. Cover and simmer 35 minutes over low heat.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable rice
directions: In skillet, melt butter and stir-fry onion, pepper and mushrooms until tender; add rice and serve with favorite meat dish.

title: bundt cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease Bundt pan generously, even if pan is Teflon-lined. The cake comes out better if the pan is greased.
Place all ingredients in mixing bowl at once and beat until smooth, about 10 minutes in all.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for about an hour (longer if needed) or the cake tests done.
Serve plain or glazed.

title: believe it or not candies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Press flat with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt margarine and brown bread cubes until lightly golden. Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and cinnamon and beat well.
Pour over bread cubes and add pineapple chunks.
Stir in up to 1/3 cup reserved juice.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach yogurt cooler
directions: Place nectar, milk and yogurt in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 2 servings (1 1/4 cup each).

title: chocolate-drop cookies
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar, milk, butter and salt in large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in flavoring and oats.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken or turkey balls
directions: Spray saucepan with cooking spray.
Make small meatballs for hors d'oeuvres, medium size for dinner with carrots, string beans and potatoes, added to the gravy.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients after cooking macaroni according to package directions.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cottage cheese lime salad
directions: In a very large bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until thickened, but not set.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 12 cup fluted tube mold. Chill until firm.
Serve on leaf lettuce bed.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings together; spread in a glass pie pan.
Add can of pizza sauce.
Layer pepperoni and then green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Add 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake for 5 more minutes. Use crackers to dip with.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (mix will be thin).
Bake in greased baking loaf dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Scrape carrots and cut in julienne strips.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup of boiling water.
Add carrots and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter in skillet; add onion and cook about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 cup water and bring to boil.
Add carrots and chicken bouillon.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Add pinch of sugar just before serving.

title: skillet cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and lightly flour iron skillet (10-inch).
Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into skillet and top with Crumble Topping.
Make indentations in the batter with your finger all the way to bottom of pan so topping will bake into cake.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: chocolate "worms"
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Remove from heat; add noodles and nuts.
Stir carefully and cover noodles completely with mixture. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; cool.
Makes about 36 to 40 pieces.

title: psari athos(monk's mackerel)
directions: Have mackerel split and cleaned and have heads and tails removed, if desired.
Rinse fish with cold water and dry well. Saute onions lightly in 1 tablespoon olive oil for about 5 minutes.
Coat flat baking dish with oil and arrange fish in one layer so it will cook evenly.
Cover fish with onions, remaining oil, herbs, seasoning and lemon juice.
Top with olives.
Cover dish with double layer of foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 1/2 hour or until fish flakes.
Serve with plain boiled potatoes. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Blend corn and milk; gradually stir in egg.
Add next 4 ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easter breakfast quiche
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
In skillet, cook ham and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until onions are tender.
Add eggs and scramble until set.
Fold mushrooms and cooked eggs into white sauce.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine melted butter, crumbles and paprika. Sprinkle on top of eggs.
Cover and chill overnight until 30 minutes before serving.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Yields 12 servings.

title: snowball jewels
directions: Combine all ingredients;
mix
well.
Drop
by
rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or
until edges are very lightly browned.
Using moistened spatula, immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: dutch stew
directions: Cut up cabbage and boil in small amount of water.
Brown the onion, celery and meat.
Simmer cabbage, tomatoes and meat mixture until flavors are well blended.
Season to taste with black pepper and salt.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 2 quarts of water.

Drain beans the next day and rinse well. Saute onions, celery and carrots in olive oil. Add beans plus 2 quarts of fresh water, ham bone and garlic. Simmer 3 hours. Add chili powder, thyme, black pepper, lemon juice and bay leaf.

Simmer for 30 minutes, while removing meat from bone, throw away fat and bone and return the meat to the soup. Add tomato sauce and simmer 45 minutes or until tomato flavor is cooked throughout the soup.

title: grandma edith nollan's cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together. Combine orange juice, grated rind, oil and enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Stir in beaten egg.
Pour into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.	Set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat until pink is gone.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 2 cups water.
Cook slowly 30 to 45 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, 2 package Mozzarella cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Layer:
noodles, cottage cheese and meat. Cook at 350°.

title: sweet pastry
directions: Mix the flour and sugar and make a hole in the middle.
Mix the shortening, butter or margarine, vanilla and egg and cut in with 2 knives or with a pastry cutter.
(May add a little water, if needed.)
Roll.
Place over tops of cups and roll to fill cups. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill with cream filling. Place a strawberry on top.

title: crab grass
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: 9 layer salad
directions: Make one day ahead.
Shred lettuce and put in bottom of bowl. Layer other ingredients:
celery, onions, green pepper, peas, salad dressing and sugar.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbled bacon on top.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: pauline's fiesta chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onions and chilies.
Mix chicken, cheese and 1/2 of soup mixture.
Spread some sauce on bottom of pan.
Place even amount of chicken mixture on each tortilla; spread across, roll up and place seam side down.
Cover evenly with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle some more cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat with pepper and onion.
Drain well.
Add tomatoes, beans and 3/4 cups water.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: hot orange cider
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed on can.
Heat orange juice and apple cider just to boiling over low heat.
Pour about 1 cup orange juice mixture into each mug.
Stir in 2 teaspoons rum, if desired.
Top with orange slice.
Garnish with stick cinnamon, if desired.
Makes 12 servings, 135 calories per serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice the green pepper and the tomatoes.
Slice mushrooms.
Mix spaghetti, tomatoes and green pepper in a bowl.
Pour on the vegetable supreme seasoning.
Add the Italian dressing.
Place in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: brunch fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine pineapple, bananas, grapes, oranges, and apples in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In a sauce pan, combine sugar, cornstarch, orange juice, lemon juice, and pineapple juice.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to a boil.	Reduce heat and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour cooled mixture over fruit and mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.	10 servings.

title: "italian" bruschetta(appetizer)
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch dice and toss with garlic and shallots.
Chop basil and add to tomatoes along with lemon juice, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup olive oil; set aside.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix the jello with hot water; let set until it begins to congeal.
Whip whipping cream and fold in other ingredients. Place in mold and let set overnight.

title: rocky mountain cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.

title: chunky brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour and sugar.
Cut in cold butter or margarine until crumbly. Press firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: diana's carrot-applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, cereal, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and raisins.
Whisk eggs in a medium size bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, vanilla, applesauce and carrots until well-blended. Add to flour mixture.
Stir just to moisten.

title: mother's enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Stir in 1 cup water, green pepper, onion and soup mix.
Simmer until liquid is reduced.
Mix Ro-Tel, mushroom soup and enchilada sauce in bowl.
Alternate layers of tortillas, ground beef mixture, green chilies, soup mixture, olives, cheese and pecans in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, ending with cheese and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields:
6 servings.

title: bar-be-que pork
directions: Cook roast until it falls off bone. Shred meat finely. Tie spices in gauze and mix with rest of the ingredients. Mix with meat and simmer on low heat for 2 hours. Remove spice bag and serve on buns.

title: southern barbecued chicken
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Dip pieces of chicken into sauce until thoroughly covered (save remaining sauce).
Wrap the chicken tightly in foil and cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and pour remaining sauce over all.
Seal tightly and cook an additional 30 to 45 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Empty pineapple into large kettle and bring almost to a boil. Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients, Cool Whip last. Pour into mold and let set overnight.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large pan.
Melt margarine with oil and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Pack tightly into a greased tube pan.
When set, take out of pan; slice, then put back into pan.
Sprinkle top with colored sugar.
(This cake mails well.)

title: hello dollies!
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add in layers, the next 4 ingredients.
Pour milk over layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool; cut into small squares.
Very rich!

title: potato casserole
directions: Crumble partly thawed hash browns in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix sour cream, milk, soup and onion together.
Pour over hash browns; sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of soup mix.
Mix crushed cornflakes with melted butter and put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas cutout cookies with frosting
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well.
Add rest of ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: low-fat pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites, one at a time; mix well.
Add milk, applesauce and vanilla.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: chicken basil linguine
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter and white wine.
Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix chicken, tomato, basil, oil, salt, pepper and cheese in bowl.
Pour over linguine that has been cooked according to package directions.
Serves 4.

title: pam's best pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until creamy.
Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well afterwards.
Fold in flour alternating with milk.
Add lemon and vanilla extracts last. Grease and flour large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Then mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar together in small bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate and let stand for a couple of hours.

title: homemade shake and bake
directions: Mix everything together.
Package in 4 to 6 freezer bags.
Use as a coating mix on chicken, pork chops, etc.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and cloves.
Beat butter for 30 seconds until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and bananas alternately to beaten mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool on rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mulled punch(olde towne alexandria christmas walk)
directions: In large pot while tea simmers, add lemonade and cloves (tied in a net, and simmer for 10 minutes in tea.
Add Tang and pineapple juice.
Taste for sweetness; add sugar, if necessary.
Simmer for 10 more minutes; pour over orange and lemon slices in metal punch bowl.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on pizza pan.
Layer chili, onions, peppers and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with nachos.

title: strawberry dessert pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto greased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack. Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl with mixer on high speed until well blended. Gently stir in strawberry Cool Whip. Spread cream cheese mixture over crust, top with strawberries. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 12 servings.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish. Bake about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix with the margarine.
Sprinkle this crumb mixture over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve either warm or cool.

title: lemon-dill chicken
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add all ingredients (except chicken).
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil, but do not actually boil.
Cover; lower heat.
Simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Serve with noodles or rice over which remaining liquid has been poured.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in brown grocery bag.
Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High until it boils.
Microwave 2 minutes more, stirring after each minute.
Remove and stir in soda.
Pour mixture over corn in bag.
Roll shut and shake well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until tender.
Drain onions and peppers. Heat soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper together in a saucepan until mixed well.
Pour over vegetables and toss until well coated.
Keep refrigerated.
Let stand overnight for best flavor.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Brush the inside of pie shell with a small amount of the beaten eggs.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake shell for 5 minutes or until light golden brown in a 425° oven for metal pan or 450° for glass plate.
Reduce temperature to 350° for metal pan or 375° for glass plate.

title: paella
directions: Heat a large paella pan or frying pan.
Add 1/4 cup oil and brown the chicken pieces.
Remove them from the pan.
Add the sausage, without the casings, the onions, garlic and ham.
Saute until the onions are clear, then add the tomatoes.
Saute for 5 minutes more and remove all from pan.
Add remaining oil to pan and add the rice, stirring over the heat until the rice begins to brown lightly.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine ingredients (except chicken) in large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add whole fryer; boil for 50 minutes, or until tender, turning once.
Use sauce as a dip when you serve chicken.

title: cranberry whipped cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add enough boiling water and syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peels.
Fold in orange and pineapple; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until set. Serves 8 to 10.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Place pasta in
large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Toss lightly. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Stir before serving. Serves 12 to 15 happy guests.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans; set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and ginger; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin, egg product and oil.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and almonds.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Let cool; wrap and store overnight.

title: chicken, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cut up chicken.
Boil and debone.
Set aside.
Steam broccoli; set aside.
Cook Uncle Ben's broccoli-rice-au gratin in chicken broth according to instructions on package.
Mix rice, broccoli and chicken together.
Add a little grated cheese and stir.
Pour mixture in buttered casserole dish and spread out.
Spread grated cheese on top of mixture.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 1 cup mayonnaise and stir.
Spread on top of cheese.
Crush cracker crumbs and mix with 3 tablespoons butter and stir.
Spread on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cracker crumbs are browned.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, drain; combine with the mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, pecans and the soup mix. Stir well. Cover and chill several hours. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: rice krispies ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except ice cream) . Put half of the mixture in bottom of a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Put ice cream on top (cut inch thick).
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover with foil and place in freezer.
Remove 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares (18).

title: homemade waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Beat eggs.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into center of hot waffle iron.
Bake about 3 to 5 minutes. Makes eight 7-inch waffles.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken and brown on both sides, 12 to 16 minutes.
Add mushrooms, wine and herbs.
Cook covered over low heat, 5 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congealed buttermilk salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a saucepan.
Add jello and dissolve on low heat.
Stir and set aside to cool.
Add buttermilk; stir well.
Add pineapple, then stir in Cool Whip topping until mixed. Pour into glass dish or Tupperware rectangle.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls, brown meat, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add pizza sauce.
Pour over crescent rolls. Top with cheese.
Put remaining rolls over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: Debone chicken breasts; cut into pieces and layer on the bottom of a 9 x 13 casserole. Take 12 corn tortillas, break into bite-size pieces and layer over chicken. Mix together soups, broth, salsa, chili and onion. Pour over chicken and tortillas; top with grated cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake for another 30 or 40 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: broccoli-cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in 1 1/2 teaspoons margarine; set aside.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over cabbage and toss.
Chill 2 hours, covered.
Then serve.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water, then lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix and chill.
Add ginger ale.
Just prior to serving, may be frozen (without adding ginger ale).
It may be partially thawed and served slushy.
Serves approximately 40 punch cups.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 10-inch pie pan lightly. Cook ground beef and onion. Stir in taco seasoning; spread in pie pan. Sprinkle with cheese and Ortega's.

title: potato in oven
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put meat in an oven roaster. Add onion, potatoes and tomatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water. Bake for about 1 hour. Serve with green peppers and radishes.

title: cherry oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix sugar, nuts, oats, margarine and flour until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remainder into bottom of 9-inch square baking dish. Stir cinnamon into pie filling.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top, pressing lightly.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: orient express chicken
directions: In a small bowl, stir first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Set aside. Generously spray a large skillet with cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat.
Add shrimp, veggies and garlic.
Stirring constantly, cook 3 to 4 minutes. Stir sauce mixture. Add to skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and margarine like for pie crust; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until light brown for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bacon cake(for breakfast)
directions: Cut bacon up in pieces and fry out.
Drain grease; place bacon in an oblong baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bacon pieces and bake until done in a 350° oven (about 25 to 30 minutes, depending on oven and size pan used).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and combine ingredients except for cheese.
Put in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Heat in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: onion cake bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare roll mix according to package directions.
While dough rises, slice onion.
Saute onion in margarine until limp and golden, about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Beat eggs and sour cream until blended.
Add salt and stir sour cream mixture into onion.
When dough has doubled, punch down and let it rest 10 minutes.
Then roll out to an 11 x 15-inch rectangle.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the dough, turning up 1-inch edge on all sides.
Pour onion mixture into the dough-lined pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until onion custard-like mixture is set. Serves 12.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and Italian seasoning.
Dip eggplant slices in beaten eggs, then in cracker crumbs to coat completely.

title: quick chicken over biscuit
directions: Place chicken, peas and carrots in pot.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Heat over low heat until bubbly.
Bake Grand biscuits according to directions.
Place biscuits on individual plates. Pour chicken mixture over biscuits in desired amounts.
Serves 4.

title: fruit and nut tropical slaw
directions: Mix pineapple juice, mandarin orange juice and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Pour over banana in a large bowl.
Add celery, cabbage, walnuts, raisins and fruit.
Add yogurt and salt; toss to mix.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Cook sausage slow, then cool and pour off fat.
Into drippings, put apple or plum jelly and liquid of pineapple that has been drained from pineapple chunks that are to be used.
Dissolve in this juice cornstarch, catsup, Worcestershire and mustard.
Warm until thickens.
Add sliced sausage and pineapple chunks.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pack in a tube cake pan which has been lined with wax paper.
Place in refrigerator 3 days before serving.

title: no bake peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the corn syrup and dry milk.
Let it stand for 20 minutes. Important.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Place shrimp in buttered casserole with tomatoes, chopped onion and green peppers.
Bake about 1/2 hour in moderate 350° oven.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck and diced onion.
At same time cover noodles with water and boil for 10-15 minutes.
Drain noodles. Add pasta sauce and garlic salt to meat.
Add noodles to meat and sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes and place in a 9 x 13 inch pan that has been greased well.
Sprinkle with half of salt and pepper, bacon and cheese and sour cream, then repeat 2nd time same way.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with chopped onions.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop up fruit and vegetables, first nuts.
Mix first 4 ingredients, then add vegetables and fruits after being drained. Refrigerate.

title: chicken tahiti
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Brown in butter.
Place in baking dish.
Add sweet and sour sauce and pineapple.
Cover and bake at 350° until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
Good with hot, cooked rice.

title: finger jello
directions: Soften gelatin in juice.
Boil water and add juice mixture gradually, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
When firm, refrigerate.
Yield: 100 little squares.

title: chili
directions: In heavy-bottomed saucepan, cook peppers, onions, garlic and bay leaves in oil, stirring frequently, until vegetables are soft. Add chili powder, salt and sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes more.
Add meat and cook until lightly brown.
Add chili peppers, tomatoes and their juice and kidney beans.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix well and put in celery sticks.

title: pea soup
directions: Combine peas, ham hocks or chopped ham, onion, thyme and water in large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Add potatoes, rutabaga, celery, leeks and salt.
Return to simmer and cook, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove ham hocks; discard skin and bones.
Chop finely and return to soup.
Sprinkle parsley or thyme on top. Makes about 15 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together the first 5 ingredients. Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Stir in the oats and the chocolate chips or other pieces.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart into ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove cookies to cooling rack.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with tortillas.
Place chicken on tortillas.
Sprinkle onion and bell pepper over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over onion mixture.
Mix soups and chili powder in bowl.
Pour over cheese. Pour tomatoes over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Let set for 15 minutes longer.

title: hot dill potato salad
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until it thickens and is bubbling. Blend in salad dressing and onion.
Fold in potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Coat beef with flour and pepper.
Brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Pour off fat.
Add thyme, basil, oregano, rosemary, marjoram, parsley, wine and water. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add more water if necessary.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 1 additional hour.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: marshann's peachy chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in a bag with the flour, salt and pepper. Brown in butter and oil. Place browned chicken in a greased 3-quart casserole dish. Combine orange juice with vinegar, sugar, basil and nutmeg. Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender, basting often. Place peach or apricot halves between the chicken pieces, basting well. Bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer. Serves 6. This is good served over rice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside; let cool.
Make graham cracker crust by mixing butter and graham cracker crumbs and pressing into a pan.
Refrigerate.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and cooled jello.
Fold in Cool Whip; pour over crust and chill.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into bite size cubes (1/2 to 1-inch).
Mix egg, flour, salt and cornstarch well, then add chicken broth to mixture.
Dip pork cubes in mixture and fry for 5 to 6 minutes in hot oil.
Drain.

title: chocolate cherry thing
directions: Mix Jell-O pudding and let set.
Pour in cherry pie mix; swirl.
Pour in whipped cream; swirl.
Chill and serve.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until brown.
Drain well.
Mix meat mixture with beans and 1 can of tomato soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Cook 25 minutes at 350°.

title: simple but good salmon patties
directions: Combine the salmon and egg in a medium size bowl.
Mix well. Add saltine crumbs and mix well. Shape into patties.
Heat oil (about 1/4 inch deep) in skillet.
Carefully place the patties into the oil. Cook over medium heat until brown on both sides.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured bread pan.
Do peel zucchini and remove seeds.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drained well.
Add to picante sauce and cheese.
Cover and let simmer over low heat until cheese is melted stirring often.
Stir until well blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Mix all together in a greased casserole dish. Cook in microwave for 17 to 20 minutes or in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised mushrooms oriental
directions: Saute mushrooms in olive oil until tender.
Stir in sugar, soy sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Add sesame oil.
Serves 6 as a side dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough well; form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese, peanut butter and Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip or pecans.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain; blot with paper towels.
Set aside while you prepare cheese filling.
(Lay drained noodles on foil until needed.)

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out dough and then roll into a tube shape.
Cut into 1/4-inch rows and unroll.
Ready for cooking.

title: spam spread
directions: Chop Spam up in food processor.
Place in bowl and stir in olives, celery, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well.
Can be served on bread for sandwiches or on crackers.

title: cran-orange delight cake
directions: Mix and then beat until smooth. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 15 minutes, remove from pans and place on wire racks and finish cooling.
Split each layer to make total of 4 layers.

title: barbecued chicken(light recipe)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix with wire whisk.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken coating chicken on both sides.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes or longer.
Grill chicken, brushing with marinade or bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting chicken while cooking. Yields 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: green gelatin salad
directions: Mix in order given and pour in casserole dish and refrigerate.

title: egg bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, bread, salt and mustard.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes or until firm at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding nuts last.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with your favorite crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and continue baking until a knife inserted will come out clean.

title: sour cream blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add and blend in the eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to the first mixture.
Add the blueberries last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Yields 24.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla. Stir with spoon until well blended and smooth. Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup morsels. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: "arch's favorite" spicy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Blend in hot sauce and spices.
Wash chicken and place in bowl.
Pour half of hot sauce glaze
over chicken and let marinate in refrigerator for at least 3
hours.
Place chicken on rack over shallow baking dish.
Brush with
glaze.
Bake, uncovered, for approximately 50 minutes.
Turn once
during
baking
and brush with glaze. Before serving, brush chicken with any leftover glaze.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut in small pieces.
Crush crackers. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 325° oven.

title: rice jumble
directions: Cut meat in cubes and fry until brown in butter.
Cut finely the onion, green pepper and celery; add to meat.
Fry until onion is soft.
Add to this the water and the rice.
Cover and cook until rice is done.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Melt oleo and sugar.
Add Chex, coconut and nuts.
Put in 2/3 of mixture into greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Set other 1/3 mixture aside.
Slice and press ice cream onto Chex.
Put rest of Chex mixture on top.
Freeze.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears; slice them.
(I quartered them and then sliced them twice again so that so that they would cook down quicker.) Cover with sugar.
Let set overnight.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, add Seven-Up last.
Bake at 305 degrees for 20 minutes.
Makes three layers.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix together and divide into 3 (8-inch) pans.
Bake in 350° oven.
Cool and fill and frost with Frosting Mix.

title: shrimp congealed salad spread
directions: Put soup in boiler
undiluted;	add
gelatine and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.	Put cream cheese and soup mix in blender (better to do half	portions
at a time) and blend. Put all in big bowl and
add
cooked shrimp, onion and celery. Fold together and put in mold.

title: quick turkey casserole
directions: Mix cream of celery soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese, turkey, and peas.
Cook noodles and fold in the above ingredients.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sesame apricot chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken in oil over medium-high heat. Add steak seasoning and preserves; mix well. Continue cooking chicken until brown and tender on low heat.
Sprinkle with sesame seed just before removing from pan.
Serve over rice or buttered egg noodles.
Use salt and pepper to taste.

title: thin sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together.
Add sweet potatoes and milk to form soft sticky dough.
Put hands under warm water from tap. Form dough into balls with hands to make biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen biscuits (2 to 3 inches each).

title: baked meat balls
directions: Mix together; then beat 1 egg with 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups crushed cracker crumbs.
Make into balls.

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Cook
and
drain
green beans.	Saute almonds in butter until lightly brown.
Add salt and toss with beans.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add and blend all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and fry to a golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash
and sliced onions together in small amount of water.
When done,
add 2 beaten eggs and cornstarch (dissolved in milk) to squash mixture.
Brown crushed bread or cracker crumbs in butter
and
sprinkle
over top.
Cook until bubbly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well with mixer.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Excellent iced with vanilla cake icing.)

title: california chicken
directions: Mix together flour and seasonings.
Dredge chicken in mixture. Brown chicken in melted butter in skillet.
Transfer to a roasting pan.
Combine juice, soy sauce and sugar; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: moist bread stuffing
directions: In large kettle, combine water, butter and onion.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Will stuff body cavity of 8-pound turkey.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken; save water.
Cut up in bite size pieces.
Melt margarine; add flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth gradually; stir constantly until thickened.
Add cream and cooking sherry.
Heat.
Combine sauce with spaghetti, mushrooms, chicken and almonds.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes (no cover).

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small cubes.
Blend together Italian dressing, mayonnaise, cream cheese, lemon juice, and salt.	Stir in chicken, eggs, celery, and almonds.
Place mixture in a 2 quart baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs with butter. Sprinkle evenly over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together. Drop spoonfuls into hot grease and cook until brown. Leftover mashed potatoes can be used.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops lightly on the stove top.
Remove from pan, then proceed to add all the other ingredients into the grease from the chops.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place chops into pan, then put sauce over chops.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a large bowl 1/2 at a time; then ice with salad dressing and sprinkle with Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for one hour.
Mix and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Place browned beef back in skillet and add Ranch Style beans, Spanish rice and picante sauce.
Heat for approximately 10 minutes.
Add half of cheese and heat another 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and garnish with remaining cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 6 people easily.
Total preparation time:
Approximately 30 minutes.
Only one skillet to wash!

title: sun-dried tomato pesto
directions: Cook pasta until tender, but still firm.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
Combine sun-dried tomatoes, cheese, basil, pine nuts and garlic in food processor or blender.
With machine running, gradually add olive oil and process until a smooth paste forms.
Combine 3/4 cup pesto with reserved liquid in same pot. Add pasta and toss to coat, adding more pesto if desired.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: debbie's tomato soup
directions: In stock pot, saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, herbs, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomato paste, brown sugar, 4 2/3 cups water and chicken bouillon.
Blend together 3 1/2 cups water and dry milk.
Add to soup and heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: more
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add cooked noodles.
Pour in casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: grandma's chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together; cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk and set aside.
Mix softened cream cheese and powdered sugar, then mix with pudding.
Last, fold in Cool Whip. Pour the mixture over cookies.
When ready to serve sprinkle the rest of the cookies over the top.

title: doritos bake
directions: Brown meat.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Lightly grease baking dish or spray with Pam.
Place Doritos in the bottom.
Add meat, beans, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
During the last 5 minutes of baking time, add the cheese to the top.

title: zucchini pudding cake
directions: Heat juice, sugar and flour stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour thickened mixture over cherries.
Mix and pour into pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust with slits cut in it. Bake until nicely browned.
Bake at 425°.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in
a 10 1/2 x 14 1/2-inch pan.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dip caps in melted butter and place upside-down in a buttered baking dish.
Chop stems and saute with onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until soft, but not brown.
Add spinach, meat, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Mix well and fill caps.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart straight sided dish.
Beat in eggs, flour and sugar.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Let stand in refrigerator severals hours or overnight.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
A wonderful side dish for ham.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a loaf.
Place into a loaf pan.
Spread ketchup lightly on top of the meat loaf.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: party cookies or old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together with a spoon.
Beat well.
Add milk, egg and vanilla to this.
Add flour.
In a piece of wax paper, roll this dough up and let chill in refrigerator for a few hours.
Place on a greased cookie sheet (cut in slices) and cook in oven at 350° until cookies are browned.
Before baking you can sprinkle candies on top for decoration (red and green sprinkles especially for Christmastime).

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack into a loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sippy soda
directions: Put ice cream into a tall glass.
Slowly add soda.
Don't let it foam over glass.
Add a straw.

title: strawberry pineapple jello
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Let cool in refrigerator until starting to set. Blend in sour cream with a whisk.
Add drained pineapple and mix, then add strawberries and blend.
Refrigerate until set.
Enjoy!

title: 4 cheese pasta and beef
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
In a skillet, brown meat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain and add tomatoes. Cook, uncovered, until slightly thickened. Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese.

title: windsor salad
directions: Put sugar, pineapple and lemon juice in saucepan.
Heat to boiling point.
Add gelatine dissolved in water to this and let cool.
Mix cream cheese with some cherry juice; blend.
Add cherries that have been cut into pieces.
When gelatine mixture is cool, add cheese/cherry mixture, then fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: biscuits for two
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Turn on to floured board and knead 1 minute.
Pat it or roll it into 1 inch thickness.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450 degrees, 10-12 minutes.
Makes 4 biscuits.

title: oyster and spinach chowder
directions: Spray a large saucepan with nonstick spray coating.
Cook onion and carrot in the saucepan over medium-high heat until onion is tender but not browned.
In a small bowl stir together 1 cup of skim milk, the flour, nonfat dry milk powder and salt; stir into vegetable mixture.
Stir in remaining milk and clam juice.
Stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in undrained oysters and spinach.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
To serve, ladle into soup bowls.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chopped onions.
Bake at 400° until cheese dip is warm and bubbly, approximately 15 minutes.
You can also add crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: pineapple turnover
directions: To make batter, cream 1/2 stick of butter with white sugar. Mix in well the egg yolks.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter; set aside.
In a cast-iron skillet, place 1/2 stick of butter in small dabs.
Add brown sugar, pouring evenly over butter.
Place 1 slice of pineapple in center of pan and other slices around, centering each with a cherry.
Pour batter over this and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 1 hour, or until done.

title: good pie crust(2-crust)
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and shortening with a pastry blender or 2 knives until shortening is cut into very small pieces.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together well; add to flour mixture.

title: taco salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce.
Brown meat and chili powder.
Drain meat.
Toss all ingredients together.
Dress salad.

title: shrimp croquettes
directions: Melt butter in large heavy pan over low heat, whisk in flour. Cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk, cook over medium heat whisking constantly until thickened and bubbly. Stir in onion and next 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 egg and shrimp, cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape shrimp mixture into 16 balls, roll in crumbs, dip in 2 beaten eggs and roll again in crumbs.
Fry croquettes in 3 inches of oil, 3 to 4 minutes, or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake in tube cake pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix the ingredients together in the order given.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
The batter keeps in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: liver pate
directions: Rinse liver in cold water and dry.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add onions and brown; add chicken livers and cook until well done. Cool.
Blend in a blender, adding chopped boiled eggs.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; chop beef.
Mix all ingredients, except parsley.
Shape into a ball; roll in parsley.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Melt chocolate; then add to sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add a little of the hot mixture to egg yolks; stir well.
Then mix all together.
Boil 2 more minutes; add vanilla and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
May top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: grilled squash
directions: Wash squash, slice into rounds.
Slice onions.
Add salt and pepper and plenty of butter.
Wrap in aluminum foil and cook on grill 15 minutes or until done.
You can cook in slow oven.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together. Add chicken and marinate several hours or overnight. bake at 350° for 1 hour with foil on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Fry meat; drain fat and add two packages taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Lay 4 large shells on bottom of pan.
Layer meat (with seasoning), cheeses, 4 more shells, meat, cheeses, etc.
End with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lo-cal skillet cabbage
directions: Combine
all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and cook over
low
heat
5	to 10 minutes.	Vegetables should be firm; 25 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: caramel covered pecans
directions: Cook water, sugar and caramel candies to a soft ball.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir well until pecans are covered.
Pour on waxed paper and separate.
Dry completely and store in tin cans or glass jar.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Beat salad dressing, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
When done, take a fork and prick top.
Combine sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Spread on top of cake.
Fix instant pudding and spread on top.
Slice bananas and place on top of pudding.
Then spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Chop the cabbage.
Stir into it the flour, salt, mustard, pepper, butter and water.
Put mixture into buttered casserole. Over it lay the slices of bacon.
Put in oven and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight in water to cover; drain Place peas in Dutch oven with ham bone, potatoes, carrots, onion, bay leaf, 4 qts. water, and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat approximately 4 hours stirring occasionally.
Remove ham bone and bay leaf.
Place soup in blender, blend well until smooth.
Taste to correct seasonings.
Reheat and serve piping hot.
Serves 10.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed on box.
Beat egg yolks, powdered sugar and butter.
Fold Cool Whip into powdered sugar mixture.
After cake cools, crumble 1/2 of the cake into a large bowl, then cover with 1/2 of the Cool Whip mixture. Top with 1/2 of the crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers.
Chill overnight. Serve and enjoy.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and salad oil.
Stir in cooled Jell-O. Use tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not open oven door.
Mix sugar and lemonade and as soon as cake is removed from oven, pour lemonade over cake.
Let cool in pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and put on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Melt butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with nuts; lightly press into batter.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Stir sugar, flour and egg together.
Add pineapple juice. Cook until thick, stirring to keep from sticking.
Cool and spread onto top of Jell-O.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool. Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add to the already prepared whipped cream. Blend well.
Spread over crust. Spread the pie filling over this.
Cool for 4 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil
sugar,
water and cornstarch, stirring constantly until thick.
Add
jello, salt and food coloring.
Let chill. Pour
over fresh berries.
Then pour in baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: famous peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan on medium heat, stirring constantly until it starts to boil.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Set the pan in cold water.
Stir in the peanut butter until well mixed.
Add the walnuts.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand until cool, then cut.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onion.
Drain.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in diced chicken.
Fold in zucchini.
Melt butter and mix stuffing mix.
Spoon 1/2 zucchini mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1/2 stuffing mix over top.
Spread rest of zucchini mix. Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press out in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: turkey or chicken fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve in Cranberry Ring made the day before.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute the mushrooms.
Do not peel or wash, just wipe with damp cloth.
Butter 3 slices white bread.
Cut into 1-inch squares and place in large casserole.
Combine mushrooms with the onion, mayonnaise, celery, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Put mixture onto bread squares.
Butter 3 more slices of bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
Put into casserole.
Mix the beaten eggs and milk; pour over mixture in casserole.
Must be refrigerated at least 1 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Blend in order given, then beat 3 to 4 minutes at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, crushed potato chips and almonds.
Place all other ingredients in a large rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Heat cream and syrup in small saucepan until boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and stir until melted.
Serve warm to dip the fruits, cake, cookies or pretzels. Keep warm in a warming dish on low setting.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. This dip lasts for hours without losing its smooth consistency.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugars and cream again.
Add eggs 1 at a time to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and sprinkle on souffle.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato nuggets
directions: On low heat mash flour into potatoes.
Dip spoon into melted margarine, then dip spoon into potato batter and form into tablespoon size nuggets.
After all nuggets are formed, melt 1/4 stick margarine and brown with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Pour over potato nuggets.

title: buddig beef cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese with two packages of Buddig beef.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, Accent and onion and mix well.
Roll the cheese ball in the remaining package of Buddig beef. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Soften the margarine to room temperature.

Beat eggs slightly. Sift flour in a large mixing bowl with all the dry ingredients. Make a hole in the flour and pour in all the other ingredients. Mix with a spoon until all is moist (do not use a mixer).
Bake in a tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Will keep in the refrigerator for weeks.

title: beef stew
directions: Dust meat with flour; brown in shortening in large pan.
Add soup and water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
To thicken, uncover.

title: easy caramels
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a heavy 3-quart pan.
Add brown sugar and salt, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Blend in corn syrup.
Gradually add condensed milk, stirring constantly. Cook and stir over medium heat until the candy reaches firm ball stage (245°).
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and pour into buttered baking dish.
Cool; cut into small squares and wrap.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain off grease. Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt with milk and eggs.
Cook until mixture coats a spoon over medium heat.
Add vanilla and cool. Place a layer of wafers and then bananas.
Then spread with filling each time.
Put on meringue and brown.

title: cherry angel trifle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; refrigerate for 15 minutes. Place half of the cake cubes in a 3-quart trifle or serving bowl. Top with half of the gelatin and pie filling. Repeat layers. Top with whipped topping. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat griddle and fry like pancakes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add onion rings and peppers.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over the carrots.
Let set 12 hours.
Keeps well.
It may be kept in the refrigerator as long as 2 weeks.

title: budget diaper wipes
directions: Put all liquids in container and add 1/2 paper towel roll. Soak 1 hour or overnight.
Keep lid on when not in use.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Trim and wash rhubarb and strawberries and cut as listed. Place in large mixing bowl adding fruit, Polaner All-Fruit jelly, honey and spices.
Mix well, add both sugars and mix well again. Add flour and mix especially well to prevent a runny pie.
Place pie crust bottoms in pie pans and add 1/2 of mix into each.
Place top crust on, pinch edges together and cut 6 air vents in crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (when sugar is boiling in crust of pie).
Remove and cool at least 4 hours before serving.

title: play dough
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable baking dish,
arrange onions; set chicken breasts, skinned side up, over onions.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave on High (100%) for 5 minutes, until chicken is cooked through.
In small mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients; spread over chicken breasts.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes until sauce is heated through.
Makes 2 servings.
Has 209 calories.

title: creamed asparagus
directions: Cook the asparagus in salt water until tender.
Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Add the beaten yolks of eggs and cook five minutes.
Pour the sauce over the asparagus and serve.

title: spicy cracker dip
directions: Mix catsup and horseradish.
Spread over cream cheese.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Excellent with Triscuits or any favorite crackers.

title: beef steak-potato scallop
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut beef into 1 inch cubes; coat with flour. Heat shortening in skillet until melted; cook beef until brown. Add onion; cook and stir until onion is tender. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with 3 tablespoons flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, thyme and garlic salt. Pour water over mixture. Cover and bake until beef is tender, 40 to 60 minutes. Increase oven temperature to 450°. Arrange potatoes on beef in layered rolls; sprinkle with salt and paprika. Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in bowl; mix well.
Pat into ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: fast cold dough
directions: Mix all ingredients for dough.
Mix with hands.
Knead a few minutes. Roll out on board which has been covered with flour and sugar.
Shape into desired shapes and fill with favorite fillings. Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.

title: tuna fish mold
directions: Mix jello and cool until syrupy.
Mix other ingredients and add to jello when syrupy.
Molds well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Mix and refrigerate ingredients. Just before serving, add bag of crushed Doritos (chips).

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: reuben melt
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: In 2-quart pan, melt caramels and butter over low heat, stirring occasionally until caramels are melted (12 to 15 minutes).
Stir in nuts, milk and rum.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients; add all the rest of the ingredients, including juice from cans of beans.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: applesauce
directions: Put apples and water in large kettle.
Simmer until apples are very soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients until sugar and candy are dissolved.
Cool.
Makes about 25 servings.
Cut some apples crosswise and find the star!

title: cottage cheese and noodles
directions: Boil the noodles according to package directions.
Melt the butter in a skillet and saut the chopped garlic, onion and parsley.
Add together the garlic, onion mixture, cooked noodles and cottage cheese.
Cool and serve cold.

title: super chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add celery and onion; simmer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add chicken and cook until heated thoroughly. Mix in tomatoes.

title: berry dips
directions: Mix 1/2 of whipped topping and orange peel in a small bowl. Mix remaining whipped topping, strawberries and yogurt in separate bowl.
Dip with whole strawberries and other fruit into each kind of dip.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican dip
directions: In pizza pan, spread can of refried beans.
Leave hole in the middle for the sour cream.
Fry up hamburger and add package of taco seasoning.
Spread this on top of refried beans.
Add chopped tomatoes, chopped onions, olives and jalapeno green peppers. Spread picante sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put dish of sour cream in middle and serve with Tostitos.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Slice and mix apples, cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix sugar, cooking oil, orange juice, vanilla and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Layer in an ungreased tube pan.
Layer batter and apples until all are used. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Separately combine flour, oatmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine dry ingredients into wet.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and Hershey bar.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: drummond rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Add butter, beef broth and almonds.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Saute onions in small amount of butter.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until transparent.
Saute mushrooms in same pan.
Add seasonings.

title: bannock bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Heat oil in heavy skillet over low fire.
Pour batter into skillet.
Cover with lid.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
When brown on bottom, turn.
Brown other side 10 to 15 minutes.

title: champion raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes, brown but still soft.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
The longer it sets the better.

title: chinese sausage
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Saute vegetables in sausage grease. Add chicken soup and rice to 4 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add to all other ingredients.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan (30 minutes covered and 15 minutes, uncovered).
No salt or pepper needed.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In 9x13 inch glass baking dish layer the ingredients as follows:
After the can of peas drained, Stop and with spatula spread 1 pt. of Mayonnaise over layers.
Sprinkle on a pinch or two of sugar to taste, just enough to take the bite out of the mayonnaise.
Then continue with the rest of the ingredients. Refrigerate - Serves 8-10.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
In medium mixing bowl, blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended. Stir in chips.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from pan.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and
pepper
in a bowl.
Stir chicken into eggs and then
place
in Bisquick mixture.
Coat chicken well. Heat oil in
