skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry chicken until golden brown
and
done.	Add
vegetables
and stir-fry until vegetables are slightly limp.	Serves 4.

title: peach salad
directions: Pour gelatin in a pan.
Pour pineapple over this and heat to dissolve.
Cool in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Add buttermilk and stir.

title: huguenot torte(bake off winner)
directions: Beat whole eggs in electric mixer or with rotary beater until very frothy and lemon colored.
Add other ingredients in above order.
Pour into 2 well buttered 8 x 12-inch baking pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until crusty and brown.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Finely chop shrimp and combine all ingredients well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and oil until light and fluffy.
Combine soda, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and zucchini.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 50-60 minutes.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift flour; mix in other dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
To this mixture, add raisins alternately with the flour; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna parmesan
directions: Meat sauce:
Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.

title: banana nut bars
directions: Break 3 ripe bananas into mixing bowl and beat until smooth. Add 1 cup sugar; mix.
Add 1/2 cup oil and mix.
Add 4 eggs and mix.
Add milk, vanilla, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add flour and mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix. Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet (12 x 17 x 1-inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
When partially cooled, glaze with powdered sugar/water mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry special
directions: Mash up strawberries in a blender.
Add heavy cream and blend for 30 seconds.
Put in serving dish.
Add whipped cream.
Serve cold.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add salt and pepper; add flour gradually.
Add enough flour to roll into long rolls and chill. Slice and bake at 350°.

title: no cholesterol oat bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well with beater.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 15 to 17 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.
Store in refrigerator in plastic bag.

title: roast tenderloin with green peppercorn sauce
directions: Place tenderloin in open roasting pan; crisscross 2 bacon slices over each.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until meat thermometer reaches 155°.
Pare fresh pineapple and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Saute pineapple; remove.
Add sugar to skillet and cook over medium heat until caramelized, about 5 minutes.
Add vinegar and chicken broth; bring to boiling and cook until sugar dissolves.
(If using canned pineapple, drain and add juice to chicken broth.)
Add peppercorns and boil rapidly to reduce to about 1 cup.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spoon olive oil into a stainless steel skillet or iron skillet to cover the bottom.
Heat the skillet on medium.
Pour the cornbread mixture into the heated skillet. Remove from the heat and place into the oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: delicious snack
directions: Mix and pour first 4 ingredients over crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.
Keeps well.

title: stuffed tomatoes with basil
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve the tomatoes and spoon their pulp into a bowl.
Place the halves, cut side down, on paper towels to dry.

title: drunken hot dogs
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and cook at a simmer for at least 1 hour, preferably two hours.
Serves 10.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Ahead of time:
Boil and debone chicken.
In skillet, heat oil.
Brown rice, onion and green pepper.
Add water, tomato sauce, chicken and spices.
Cover and simmer until water is gone.

title: hamburger & cabbage skillet meal
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet and drain. Add next 4 ingredients. Add chopped cabbage over top. Cook until cabbage is just tender.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well except potato chips.
Spread chips on top.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° to 450° oven.
Serves 5.

title: dry jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Put dry Jell-O in bowl.
Add cottage cheese first; add Cool Whip, then fruit.
Let set to firm.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup of the coconut and the eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend and then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together very well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in the 4 cups cooking oil until golden brown.
Makes 50 hush puppies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage soften to room temperature.
Knead together cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Form into small balls. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add onion and saute until tender.
Drain spinach. Add to onion and cook only until moisture evaporates. Cool. Beat eggs on low speed of mixer. Add cheese. Stir in onion and spinach mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Top should be nicely browned and tester come out clean.

title: frozen summer salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt.
Fold in cream, oranges, dates, pineapple and ginger.
Turn into an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Freeze for 1 hour or until firm. Let stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes to soften before cutting into squares.
Serve with salad greens of your choice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar and egg together.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grate cheese very fine.
Cheese and margarine should be at room temperature.
Mix by hand.
Use the star design on cookie press.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
tags: extra sharp New York State aged cheese

title: lentil soup
directions: In
a
large saucepan, saute the bacon, carrots, onions and celery in oil until the onion and celery are transparent. Add flour;
stir constantly.
Slowly add water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer approximately 3 hours.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Prepare jello.
Using 1 cup jello, mix in all fruit, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
This goes with chicken, turkey or pork.

title: old-fashioned bread dressing
directions: Combine bread crumbs and poultry seasoning and toss together. Melt butter in skillet; add celery and onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk, salt and pepper, then add the sauteed onion and celery to bread crumbs.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir well and pour into pan and bake for about 45 minutes.
Enough for 5 1/2 or 6 pound roasting chicken.
Also, spray the pan with Pam so the dressing won't stick in the pan and the pan can be easily washed.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until golden brown (about 1 to 1 1/4 hours).
This makes 10 to 15 slices.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of warm water; add sugar.
Allow yeast to proof (foam) about 10 minutes.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups water, salt and 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add flour 1 cup at a time until mixture forms a ball (you may not need all the flour). Knead dough on floured work surface for 5 to 10 minutes until shiny and elastic.

title: squash supreme
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter until tender.
Add all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Put in buttered dish and top with crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 cake pan.
Dice uncooked rhubarb into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, add to butter mixture.
Add rhubarb and sour cream.
Blend well.
Batter will be thick.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Combine topping ingredients, sprinkle over top.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Can easily double or triple this recipe.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and add sugar gradually; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda and add to creamed cheese mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla, pecans, coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix ingredients, except margarine, well; put into baking dish. Dot with 1 stick of margarine that has been cut into small squares.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: avocado dip
directions: In medium bowl, with mixer, at low speed, gradually beat the soup into the cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in the onion and chili powder.
Mash the avocado.
Beat into the soup mixture. Serve with assorted raw vegies.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pickled pink eggs
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, cloves, peppers, allspice and salt to a boil.
Add juice from beets and simmer for 3 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Remove from heat and cool.
Layer beets, shelled eggs and onions in a glass jar (with a tight lid).
Pour pickling liquid over all.
Cover jar tightly and refrigerate.
Pickling takes at least 2 days.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine and store in airtight container.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes 50 servings.

title: mrs. decker's peanut brittle
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to 230°.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 300°. Add last three ingredients.
Pour out on buttered marble slab. Stretch and pull until thin.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out dough into large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples. Sprinkle apples evenly over dough.
Roll up dough, jelly roll fashion.
Dampen edge of dough and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted margarine. Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls. (This looks like too much liquid, but crust will absorb it.) Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Add chopped cucumbers, onions and peppers, then return to a boil for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Mix soup and cheese. Add cooked rice and drained broccoli and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Place margarine on top of rice until it melts. Add corn, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crust from bread; cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Melt cheeses and oleo in top of double boiler over hot water until of rarebit consistency.
Remove from heat; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture until well coated; place on greased baking sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until puffy and golden brown.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Toss well.
Add potatoes. Cover and bake at 425° for 1 hour, stirring at 15 minute intervals.
Top with Parmesan.
Serves 12.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place in baking dish and fan them slightly. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Check with a fork.

title: "mom's meat loaf"
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Take another 1/4 cup steak sauce and 1 tablespoon mustard and mix. Brush on both meat loaves.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, salt, garlic and chili powder.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas; then 1/2 of meat mix, 1 layer onions, 1 layer cheese, 1 layer tomatoes, 1 layer chilies and 1 layer chicken soup.
Should make 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cody's fruit salad
directions: Mix peach pie filling, pineapple tidbits, strawberries and bananas.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: spice-rubbed london broil
directions: Preheat grill to medium. Combine the brown sugar, coriander, garlic, olive oil, chili powder, ground ginger, black pepper and salt in a small bowl; mix well. Rub the brown sugar mixture on both sides of the steak. Grill steak 8-inches from heat for 15 minutes, turning once.
Cut diagonally across the grain into 1/4-inch slices.

title: peanut carrot pineapple holiday bread
directions: Sift
flour,
soda,
salt and cinnamon together.
Place eggs and
sugar	in
mixer
bowl.
Beat	at medium speed until mixed. Beat in
oil, a small amount at a time.
Stir in flour mixture, carrots, pineapple, vanilla and peanuts.
Pour batter in two greased loaf pans.	Makes 2 small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: fresh homemade vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients in 6 quart saucepot.
Add 1 quart water. Bring to a
boil;	reduce	to
medium
heat and cover. Cook 2 hours,
stirring
occasionally.
Adjust
seasoning	to taste. Serve with cornbread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bacon and lettuce stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut the top off each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seed.
Salt inside of each tomato.
Invert tomatoes and drain 15 minutes.
In a small bowl combine the remaining ingredients.
Fill each tomato with mixture.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer on 12-inch platter in order given. Sour cream should cover top with cheese and olives used as sprinkles.
Chill. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: garden relish
directions: Skin and coarsely chop tomatoes.
Chop all vegetables and combine with tomatoes in a large colander.
Let drain 3 to 4 hours.

title: susan's salad
directions: Cut cheese and tomatoes into 1/4-inch chunks.
Mix with corn. Chill. Serve with your favorite dressing or as is.

title: cherry pizza dessert
directions: Mix together brown sugar, coconut and butter or oleo. Sprinkle 2/3 over crust.
Add cherry pie filling and 3/4 cup chopped nuts.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, pack in loaf pan leaving space around the edge for it to drain.
Cover loaf with catsup.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar gradually until thick.
Add rest of ingredients and then put in ice cream freezer.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and ham in buttered baking dish.
Stir milk into mushroom soup.
Add onion, salt and pepper to mushroom mixture and mix well.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover dish.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Place ingredients on skewer:
meat, onion, mushrooms, pepper and pineapple.
Repeat.
Baste with Teriyaki Sauce.
Broil about 20 minutes, turning and brushing with marinade every 5 minutes or grill on gas or charcoal.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, grate sweet potato as finely as possible.
Add milk until mixture is real mushy.
Add the eggs (slightly beaten), sugar, oleo (soft), vanilla and nutmeg; mix well.
Bake in medium baking dish in a slow oven (325° to 350°) until pudding candies around edge (approximately 1 hour).

title: modeling dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir in water and oil and heat 3 to 5 minutes until a ball forms in the pan.
Remove to a floured surface and knead for one minute.
Store in a plastic bag or airtight container in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except pecans. Blend well. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted half way between center and edge comes out clean.

title: nut roll
directions: On medium heat melt margarine and marshmallows.
Remove from heat; add milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and all of graham cracker crumbs except 1 cup.
(May have to use hands to mix.) When mixed well, place on foil on remaining crumbs and roll into the shape of a log roll.
Refrigerate.
Slice as desired.

Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, chili powder, salt and garlic powder. Combine all ingredients except tortilla chips.
Break chips in half.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce mixture, chips and beef mixture; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese until melted.

title: venison with sour cream
directions: In skillet with fat, brown venison and garlic on all sides and arrange in dish.
Put vegetables in remaining fat and cook for 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Pour over meat.
Bake in slow oven until meat is tender.
Melt butter or oleo in frying pan and add flour.
Add water meat was cooked in; boil until thick. Add sour cream and more salt, if needed.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Serve with buttered noodles.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Stir in enough flour to make batter stiff and workable.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at about 400° until cookies are slightly browned.

title: apple salad
directions: Layer ingredients with pineapple on top of apples.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: buckeyes
directions: Form into balls.
Refrigerate until solid.
Stick toothpicks into each one and dip in melted chocolate.
Refrigerate.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Stir Velveeta and salsa in saucepan over low heat until Velveeta is melted, then add ???.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix the yeast with the warm water and a teaspoon sugar.
Allow the yeast to dissolve; set aside for 5 to 10 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the yeast mixture; mix well.
Add sorghum; blend in.
Stir in flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until double its bulk.
Make into 2 loaves; place in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in the bottom of a glass pyrex pan. Open can of chili and spread that over the cream cheese and heat in the microwave oven for about 7-8 minutes.
After the chili is hot, spread cheddar cheese over and microwave until the cheddar cheese is pretty well melted.
Serve with chips.
It's a great and easy party dish!

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 large baking sheets.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir with rubber spatula until blended and dissolved.
Make sure stays warm.
Use a wooden spoon and stir in sugar, salt and 3 1/2 cups flour until a soft and slightly sticky dough forms.
Put dough on well-floured board and knead 5 to 7 minutes, adding 1/2 cup flour.
Cut dough in half, then into sixths.
Make shapes or roll into 15-inch ropes for traditional pretzels.
In small bowl, mix egg and water; brush on pretzels and sprinkle with salt.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Have butter and cheese at room temperature.
Cream together and fold in dry ingredients.
Mix.
Divide into 3 rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: delicious fried chicken
directions: Take cut-up chicken and put in large bowl.
Pour buttermilk over chicken.
Let set for 3 or 4 hours in refrigerator.
Drain off buttermilk; salt and pepper to taste.
Take chicken and roll in flour.

title: caraway bread
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Then add egg.
Mix and sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add caraway seed, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Put into prepared pan and sprinkle with extra caraway seed and sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hawaiian cream cake
directions: Bake one yellow cake mix in a greased and floured 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together the cream cheese, vanilla instant pudding and 1 cup milk.
Spread this mixture on top of the cooled cake.
Sprinkle the crushed pineapple over pudding cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish with coconut and chopped nuts.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix celery, water chestnuts and soup in a greased casserole dish.
Top with butter and cracker mix.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter with the sugar.
Add 2 eggs, vanilla and soda, sifted with the flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of a glass or with the end of a spoon.
Mark with a fork in a crisscross fashion.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: fir tip jelly
directions: Wash fir tips and bring to a boil in water. Then simmer for 1/2 hour.
Strain juice several times.
Yields 4 cups.

title: hobo beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Let cool and crumble.
Brown ground beef with onions and bacon; drain any grease.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well, then add meat mixture and stir.
Put into greased casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs until creamy. Mix in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Preheat oven to 400°.
Put 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in bag. Roll cookies, shake in bag and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken
directions: Boil the chicken until it is tender and then you debone it and mix with noodles.
Let them cook until they are tender and then add cheese and stir until cheese melts; let it simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: bacon and egg fried rice
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, in small saucepan over medium-low heat, cook bacon until browned.
Remove to paper towels to drain.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat egg substitute or eggs and salt and set aside.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, gently stir rice until well coated with oil.
Cook eggs in small amount of oil in a skillet, stirring eggs constantly, until they are set and about the size of peas.
Then gently stir rice and eggs to mix.
Spoon rice mixture into bowl; sprinkle with cooked bacon and green onion.
Makes 4 servings. Each serving about 570 calories, 16 g. fat and 5 mg cholesterol.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt morsels in condensed milk.
Add the oleo and salt.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
In a large bowl, combine the dry roasted peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into mixture. Mix well.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 2 hours.

title: rebecca's christmas bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and cereal and pour peanut butter mixture over it.
Blend together with hands and form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate pieces with a little paraffin wax.
Dip balls and place on wax paper.
Makes about 100.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper until tender, using the oleo.
Fry meat slowly until slightly brown.
Add to vegetables. Add soup, salt and pepper.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Add noodles over top of casserole.
Bake for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put spaghetti sauce on top, if desired, and continue baking for 5 minutes more.
Add pepperoni, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Cook, stirring until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and eggs.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: wedding or shower punch
directions: *Both should be same flavor.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter in double boiler.
Mix in sugar and crumbs.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin in double boiler.
Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Cut into small squares while warm.

title: mexican biscuit casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and drain off fat.
Add onions.
Cook pasta until tender.
Add to hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with 8 ounces of Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 minutes or until bubbly and melted.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Let cool and slice into squares.
Store in covered dish.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid.
Fold in berries and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes about 30 muffins.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix uncooked rice and soup (condensed) together. Pour into baking dish. Thaw chicken. Season with garlic and lemon pepper. Cut into chunks. Put chicken on top of rice mix.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: allie's cream cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese and sugar.
Add flour, salt and rind.
Beat.
Add vanilla, eggs and sour cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl with cover.
Chill thoroughly and serve.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted and blended.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(For thinner pieces, pour fudge into 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.)
Score in squares while warm; cut when firm.
Makes 3 dozen (1 1/2-inch) pieces.

title: potato asparagus soup
directions: Drain asparagus; reserve liquid.
In medium pan, saute onion and margarine.
Stir in reserved asparagus liquid, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in potatoes.
Blend well.
Add asparagus, half and half, dill and pepper.
Return to heat.
Heat slowly.
Stir frequently.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese, and powdered sugar in a mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip and combine with the first mixture.
Put 1/3 of cookies in bottom of a clean flower pot.
Add a layer (1/2) of pudding mixture.
Repeat ending with cookie mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Decorate with a plastic or silk flower.
Variations:
You can add gummy worms with some sticking out of cookie mixture.
Also you can use French vanilla pudding.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar; press in pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown, about 20 minutes. Place half of berries in baked crust.
Add sugar and cornstarch to remaining berries; boil until clear and thick.
Cool slightly; pour over berries in crust.
Cool; cover with whipped cream and serve.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening and the 2 cups sugar. Add molasses and eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well and cover; chill.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: *Do
not
use
chocolate drink.
For a richer chocolate flavor, chocolate syrup may be added to the milk.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper or pour in dish and cut.

title: no fat salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over shredded romaine lettuce and 1 chopped tomato.

title: roast to boast about
directions: You will need a large crock-pot or slow cooker.
Prick the roast and sprinkle with meat tenderizer. Place all veggies in the pot. Sprinkle a little soup mix, then place meat on top. Add water and cover. Cook on low setting for 7 hours.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and margarine.
Blend in flour.
Pour in floured cake pan.
Put in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool and ice or top with your favorite fruit.

title: chocolate marble squares
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and oleo.
Put into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Cut ice cream into slices and layer over crust.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla. Mixture will be very stiff. Roll into small balls. Chill overnight in the freezer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat until smooth.
Add bananas, flour, baking soda and walnuts; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Pour an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over loaf.
You can use ketchup, if you like.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ann's broccoli casserole
directions: Soften Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350°.
(Big pie shell, bake 45 minutes, 2 small pie shells, bake 30 minutes.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In large bowl mix sour cream and mayonnaise, relish, onion, cucumber and green pepper.
Toss gently the macaroni with dressing mixture.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Add flour and dry ingredients, Mix well.
Add crushed pineapple and bananas.
Mix. Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Mix by hand not a mixer.
Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours in a greased Bundt pan.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: iced cake
directions: Mix in bottom of pan: brown sugar, cocoa and water. Add nuts if desired. Spoon a chocolate cake mix over this.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in 1 cup of the cheese until melted. Combine macaroni and cheese mixture.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; add salt.
Drain well.
Combine all other ingredients except crumbs.
Blend with broccoli and put in buttered casserole dish.
Put crumbs on top and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: toasted finger rolls
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with undiluted soup.

Do not use a heavy coat of soup. Roll bread from corner to corner and wrap a piece of bacon (usually half a slice) around each roll, holding in place with a toothpick. Place rolls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until golden brown, about 35 minutes. Serve with soup or salad or use as an appetizer.
May be frozen.
Makes 8 servings.

title: el paso pilaf(add meat if you must)
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in oil over medium heat, about 15 minutes until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato slices.
Bring to boil; reduce and simmer about 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Serve over tomato slices.

title: indian-style grilled chicken
directions: With fork tines, pierce chicken liberally on the meaty sides, then with a sharp knife, make 1/2-inch deep diagonal cuts about 1-inch apart.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Set aside.

title: turkey wild rice casserole
directions: Place turkey, mushrooms, carrot, broccoli and broth in saucepan.
Cover; heat on medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish; keep hot.
In same saucepan, prepare rice according to package directions.
Stir in turkey mixture and Swiss cheese.
Return to casserole and place in preheated 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and top with green onions.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine pudding.
Mix with milk in bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
With 1st layer, graham crackers, then pudding mix, then graham crackers until all are used, beginning and ending with graham crackers. Spread icing on top layer.
Chill overnight.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook the spinach and drain well. Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour. Make meatball size balls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 15-20 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger; drain grease.
In large pan, put can tomato soup, can stewed tomatoes, mixed vegetables (juice and all).
Dump in envelope of onion soup.
Add hamburger.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat until hot.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Add coconut for coconut pie; add 3 tablespoons cocoa for chocolate pie or crushed pineapple for pineapple pie.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Mix sugar, marmalade, lemon juice and walnuts.
Spread all over cranberries.
Cover with foil; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and granulated sugar together in baking dish.
Top with oatmeal, brown sugar and butter, which have been combined together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Uncover for last 15 minutes to allow to brown.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with soup; place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place slices of cheese over hamburger until it's completely covered.
Cover with canned biscuits evenly.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef with onions and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening or oleo and sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir flour into mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
